(39,	20110818085132,	NULL,	'Charleston, WV: At the Entrance to Whitewater Rafting Country',	'Just East of Charleston are two premiere whitewater river destinations, The New River and the Gauley, Charleston sits just one hour from both.&nbsp; Charleston is situated perfectly to spend a day on the river and return to Charleston for an evening in the beautiful historic downtown.<br />One of the top ten whitewater runs in the world, the Gauley River, otherwise known as &ldquo;The Beast of the East&rdquo;.&nbsp; The Gauley has a short season in the fall, only 22 days, but it calls the world&rsquo;s best rafters to its banks.&nbsp; The test of skills ranges from big Class V rapids along the upper Gauley and over 40 other rapids along the Lower Gauley. <br />The New River falls just southeast of Charleston- a national park like no other with three terrific seasons of rafting- Spring, Summer and Fall.<br />The melting snows and runoff in the Spring creates a beast of the New River with the wildest rafting season and cold water splashing you the entire trip.&nbsp; In Summer, the water level drops bringing normal flows, this in addition to the sunny weather makes for swimming and visiting the historic ruins along the river a truly delightful experience!&nbsp; Fall brings a lower level to the river with calming whitewater, with the trees beginning to change makes for a picturesque experience, with all attention and excitement leading up to the arrival of Bridge Day!&nbsp; The third Saturday in October each year is the largest gathering of BASE jumpers and rapellers as they drop from the New River Gorge Bridge for this one day each year.&nbsp; <br />Start or finishing your trip in beautiful downtown of Charleston can be the perfect complement to such outdoor adventures.',	0,	0,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	0),
(40,	20110818085200,	NULL,	'Southridge Shopping',	'With over 100 shops, attractions and restaurants, Southridge offers the best shopping and dining experience in the Charleston, WV area.&nbsp; Whatever you&rsquo;re looking for, it is sure to be found in the numerous choices of dining styles, from family fun at Chuck E Cheese, to deli-style at Panera Bread or Penn Station, to full service dining at Red Lobster or Olive Garden, just to name a few.<br />&nbsp;<br />The shopping at Southridge can&rsquo;t be beat!&nbsp; A mix of stores make for a &ldquo;one-stop shopping experience.&rdquo;&nbsp; Major all-purpose chains, such as Wal-mart and Target serve as anchor stores amongst clothing stores, like Kohls and Fashion Bug and home d&eacute;cor and improvement stores like Home Depot, Big Sandy, Lowes, Pier 1 and Home Goods.&nbsp; Specialty stores also include, the Mole Hole and English Rose Bridal.<br />&nbsp;<br />We are now also welcoming our newest neighbor- Best Buy- which opened November 2010.',	0,	0,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	0),
(41,	20110818085258,	NULL,	'Recreation Near Charleston, WV',	'Between hiking the wildflower-laden trails in Kanawha State Forest, running or riding through the backwoods over the Hatfield-McCoy Trails, or the rapids of the New River Gorge, you&rsquo;ll find the best place starts in Charleston, WV.&nbsp; Centrally located to the state and at the intersection of I-64, I-77 and I-79, Charleston is the epicenter for many of the best trips for outdoor recreation the state has to offer.<br />Just minutes from the city is the 9300 square acre Kanawha State forest, home to walking trails, camping, swimming, biking, or even cross country skiing, hours or days can be easily spent here.&nbsp; The State Forest is Charleston&rsquo;s little oasis of outdoor relaxation away from the city, but still nearby for convience.<br />Also located nearby is the trailhead for one of the 6 current Hatfield-McCoy ATV trails- the Little Coal River Trail.&nbsp; Just 20 miles south of the city is the northernmost trail in the system.&nbsp; This trail is popular due to its easy level traits, with just 6% of it being marked as most difficult.&nbsp; The Little Coal River Trail is located very near family, and summer seasonal activities.<br />The Rapids of the New River Gorge can offer a wetter, more adventurous trip, just an hour&rsquo;s drive SE of Charleston.&nbsp; An abundant number of rafting companies exist around Fayetteville to offer the best experience running the rapids.&nbsp; Whether it be the Lower New River for a more exciting skill testing trip with Class III or Class V rapids, or staying in the Middle New River for more gentle waves and beginner rapids.<br />If neither is edgy enough, you can run the Gauley!&nbsp; The lower Gauley is full of waves and wide drops with an intermediate level introduction to big white water.&nbsp; The upper Gauley is one of the top 10 rated whitewater runs in the world!&nbsp; With this fast moving and technically difficult Upper Gauley whitewater rapids you are sure to have a heart stopping time!',	0,	0,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	0),
(42,	20110818090017,	NULL,	'West Virginia Cultural Center',	'The Culture Center is a contemporary companion to the State Capitol, opening in 1976 to showcase West Virginia&rsquo;s unique artistic, cultural, and historic heritage.&nbsp; The lower level of the WV State Museum recently re-opened after a complete renovation.&nbsp; You can also view the art and history exhibits in the Lobby and the Balcony Galleries; browse through State Archives library, see an NPR Mountain Stage broadcast, or join in one of the dozen exciting festivals and events held throughout the year. <br />&nbsp;<br />The Culture Center houses the offices of the Commission on the Arts and the State Historic Preservation Office, as well as the State Museum, State Archives and other administrative staff.<br />&nbsp;<br />Culture Center Hours<br />The State Museum hours are 9:00am to 5pm Tuesday through Saturday; last entry at 4:15. 12 to 5pm Sundays; last entry at 4:15.Closed on Monday<br />&nbsp;<br />The Archives Library hours are?9:00am to 5:00pm Monday through Wednesday?9:00am to 8:00pm Thursday?9:00am to 5:00pm Friday and Saturday?Closed on Sunday<br />The Culture Center offices are open Monday through Friday from 8:30am to 5pm.<br />WV Division of Culture and History?The Culture Center?Capitol Complex?1900 Kanawha Boulevard East?Charleston WV 25305-0300',	0,	0,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	0),
(43,	20110818090106,	NULL,	'Mardi Gras Casino - Where It\'s Always a Party!',	'Love the never-ending party of New Orleans?&nbsp; Then you\'ll love the Mardi Gras WV Casino- themed gaming area offering non-stop excitement!<br />&nbsp;<br />Our West Virginia casino is like no other.&nbsp; With daily and hourly winners throughout the casino, to video and reel to progressive jackpots, you can experience it all here at our local casino &amp; resort!&nbsp; There are 70 different varieties of your favorite games and the high-tech machines with TITO (Ticket in Ticket out) will make your cashing out experience much easier.<br />&nbsp;<br />Featuring 31 Table Games including:<br />Blackjack- $3 Blackjack Monday-Friday 11am-4pm<br />Roulette- spin the wheel and discover your fortune<br />Craps- this fast moving casino game will be sure to keep you on your toes<br />Big Six- use your strategy to beat the odds<br />&nbsp;<br />Also try your hand at Three-Card Poker, Four-Card Poker, Let it Ride Poker or Spin the Big 6 wheel- hit the right symbol for a big payoff.<br />&nbsp;<br />Between 90,000 square feet of gambling entertainment and more than 1,200 slots there is never a dull moment!&nbsp; The New Orleans vibe will keep you in the party mood. <br />&nbsp;<br />Watch Live Racing and Get Greyhound Racing Results<br />The excitement doesn\'t stop in the casino, capture the thrill of breathtaking Greyhound racing as you dine on a succulent steak or seafood at our First Turn Restaurant while watching the races or as you eagerly wait for the final Greyhound racing results to be announced.&nbsp; Mardi Gras Casino is one of the only West Virginia racing establishment that allows you to bet, dine and wine- all in one place!<br />&nbsp;<br />-LIVE dog track race Monday, Wednesday- Sunday at 7:30pm and a special performance matinee at 1:30pm on Saturday<br />-Bet on your favorite tracks in one of our many state-of-the-art simulcast areas<br />-Dine at First Turn, overlooking our vast racetrack<br />-Get Greyhound racing results right at your table',	0,	0,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	0);
