(168,	2,	'2015-06-22 16:29:10',	'2015-06-22 20:29:10',	'<strong>What: </strong>Firecracker 5K Run/Walk\r\n\r\n<strong>Who</strong>: Any runner or walker who would like to participate in a Fourth of July 5K that raises money and awareness for a good local cause\r\n\r\n<strong>When and Where</strong>: Friday, July 3, 6:00 PM, Downtown Charleston with the course running down Kanawha Boulevard right before Live on the Levee.\r\n\r\n<strong>Why</strong>: To raise funds to provide free speech, language, feeding and swallowing therapy to almost 90 children in eight different counties West Virginia\r\n\r\n<strong>Age Divisions and Prizes: </strong>There will be a top three in each age category, as well as a top male and female runner overall. There will also be a top three in the overall walking category. Each participant will get a Runners Bag for entering the event\r\n\r\n<strong>Price and Registration</strong>: A participant can either register online or by mailing in the race application.  There will also be same day registration at the event. The registration prices are:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class=\"li1 first\">$15 for registered on or before May 15</li>\r\n	<li class=\"li1\">$20 for registered on or before June 15</li>\r\n	<li class=\"li1 last\">$25 for registered on or before July 3</li>\r\n</ul>',	'Firecracker 5K Run/Walk',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'firecracker-5k-runwalk',	'',	'',	'2015-06-22 16:29:10',	'2015-06-22 20:29:10',	'',	0,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/?post_type=chronosly&#038;p=168',	0,	'chronosly',	'',	0),
