(189,	3,	'2015-06-30 08:22:44',	'2015-06-30 12:22:44',	'<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\r\n<h4>Best Events for the Foodie</h4>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_360\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"210\"]<img class=\"wp-image-360\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/taste_of_all1-300x230.jpg\" alt=\"taste_of_all1\" width=\"210\" height=\"161\" /> Taste-of-All. Photo Credit: FestivAll[/caption]\r\n<h3>Smoke on the Water Chili Cookoff</h3>\r\nChili cooks compete to see who has the best red, green and home-style chili and salsa. Kids activities, frozen t-shirt and hot pepper eating contests, live music, local food vendors and plenty of cold drinks. Proceeds benefit HospiceCare.\r\n<h3>Mac and Cheese Cookoff</h3>\r\nMac and Cheese enthusiasts enter and taste the Charleston area\'s best Macaroni and Cheese. Proceeds benefit the Childhood Language Center of Charleston, WV.\r\n<h3>Taste-of-All</h3>\r\nTaste-of-All Charleston is a tour of the culinary talents and amazing cuisine available throughout Charleston, WV. Fun for the whole family, visitors can taste amazing dishes served by some of\r\nthe gifted chefs and restaurants from the valley.\r\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\r\nSpring, summer and fall are perfect for outdoor dining but all year-round is great for those special Charleston places that love to serve you!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-container-cb\">\r\n<h2>You dont have to look very far to find great cuisine in Charleston! We have highlighted just a few of the amazing places you can go to have a casual meal, a quick bite, a fancy feast or make your own!</h2>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-1-cb\">\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1212 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/DC_Button_A.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />Bluegrass Kitchen</h3>\r\nFarm-to-table comfort food with a modern edge. Specialties are vegetarian &amp; omnivorous dishes made from ingredients naturally sourced within WV and the Appalachians served in a dining room restored to its circa 1920\'s beauty.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">1600 Washington St E\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\n<a href=\"http://www.bluegrasswv.com/\" target=\"_blank\">bluegrasswv.com</a></p>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/see-do/foodie\" target=\"_blank\"><button style=\"font-family: \'roboto_slabbold\';\">SHARE</button></a>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1229 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/DC_Button_9-C.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />Charleston Bread Company</h3>\r\nBreads, cookies, pastries and more baked fresh every day.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">601 Capitol St.\r\nCharleston, West Virginia 25301</p><br /><br />\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/see-do/foodie\" target=\"_blank\"><button style=\"font-family: \'roboto_slabbold\';\">SHARE</button></a>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1233 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/DC_Button_9-E.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />The Block</h3>\r\nThe Block offers cocktails and small bites complimented by views of downtown Capitol St. The restaurant features an active cheese cave and glass enclosed wine cellar. Jazz music on selected nights.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">201 Capitol St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.theblockwv.com/\" target=\"_blank\">theblockwv.com</a></p>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/see-do/foodie\" target=\"_blank\"><button style=\"font-family: \'roboto_slabbold\';\">SHARE</button></a>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1230 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/DC_Button_9-G.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />Capitol Market</h3>\r\nBuilt from an 1800s railroad transfer dock, the market serves as an indoor/outdoor farmer\'s market, home of a variety of specialty shops and Sohos restaurant. The Charleston CVB also has a satellite site at the market.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">800 Smith Street\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.capitolmarket.net/\" target=\"_blank\">capitolmarket.net</a></p>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/see-do/foodie\" target=\"_blank\"><button style=\"font-family: \'roboto_slabbold\';\">SHARE</button></a>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1235 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/DC_Button_9-I.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />JQ Dickenson Salt Works</h3>\r\nDescendants of the original salt makers in the Kanawha Valley produce clean, artisinal salt, harvested by hand. Tours are available with reservations.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">371 Kanawha Salines Dr.\r\nMalden, WV 25306\r\n<a href=\"http://www.jqdsalt.com/\" target=\"_blank\">jqdsalt.com</a></p>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/see-do/foodie\" target=\"_blank\"><button style=\"font-family: \'roboto_slabbold\';\">SHARE</button></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1232 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/DC_Button_9-B.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />Black Sheep Burritos</h3>\r\nLocated in the heart of downtown, Black Sheep offers an eclectic mix of tex-mex menu items and Charleston Brewing Company beer. One of the best brunch menus in the Kanawha Valley.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">702 Quarrier St,\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.blacksheepwv.com/\" target=\"_blank\">blacksheepwv.com</a></p>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/see-do/foodie\" target=\"_blank\"><button style=\"font-family: \'roboto_slabbold\';\">SHARE</button></a>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1234 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/DC_Button_9-D.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />Ellen\'s Ice Cream</h3>\r\nEllens Homemade Ice Cream was born over 15 years ago with the simple mission to delight customers with all-natural, high-quality ingredients and a welcoming and comfortable atmosphere.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">225 Capitol St,\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://ellensicecream.com/\" target=\"_blank\">ellensicecream.com</a></p>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/see-do/foodie\" target=\"_blank\"><button style=\"font-family: \'roboto_slabbold\';\">SHARE</button></a>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1236 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/DC_Button_9-F.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />West Side Farmers Market</h3>\r\nThe purpose and mission of the market is to educate about local food resources and to revitalize the community by creating a vibrant market at which local farmers and home gardeners may sell their produce.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">303 Washington St. West\r\nCharleston, WV 25302\r\n<a href=\"http://wsfmcharleston.com/\" target=\"_blank\">wsfmcharleston.com</a></p>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/see-do/foodie\" target=\"_blank\"><button style=\"font-family: \'roboto_slabbold\';\">SHARE</button></a>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1231 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/DC_Button_9-H.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />Butter it Up!</h3>\r\nEver had butter in your coffee? This is a must-try. Butter it up! is a gluten free coffee shop. They offer paleoish breakfast, lunch, and dinner options in addition to local products.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">714 Virginia St E,\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/butteritupcrw\" target=\"_blank\">facebook.com/butteritupcrw</a></p>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/see-do/foodie\" target=\"_blank\"><button style=\"font-family: \'roboto_slabbold\';\">SHARE</button></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n<div><iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/embed?mid=zF2Ov4mSNUbs.kJ6jMMcM14rs\" width=\"460\" height=\"325\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>',	'Foodie',	'',	'publish',	'open',	'open',	'',	'foodie',	'',	'',	'2015-08-17 15:21:06',	'2015-08-17 19:21:06',	'',	8,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/?page_id=189',	0,	'page',	'',	0),
