(241,	3,	'2015-06-29 10:11:33',	'2015-06-29 14:11:33',	'<h2><a href=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/volleyball4.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-240\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/volleyball4-300x177.jpg\" alt=\"volleyball4\" width=\"300\" height=\"177\" /></a>Adrenaline Junkie</h2>\r\n<h3>Climb zip, row and ride through the Charleston West Virginia area with these great heart-</h3>\r\n<h3>pumping activities.</h3>\r\nAdventures on the Gorge\r\n\r\nAOTG offers a variety of adrenaline pumping adventures including whitewater rafting on the\r\n\r\nNew and Gauley Rivers, canopy tours, zip lines, guided hiking, paintball, caving, horseback\r\n\r\nriding and more! With restaurants and kids camps, the whole family can really make a day of it!\r\n\r\n219 Chestnutburg Rd.\r\n\r\nLansing, WV 25862\r\n\r\nwww.adventuresonthegorge.com\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nHatfield and McCoy Trails\r\n\r\nEight trail systems stretch over 700 total miles of West Virginia allowing UTV, ATV, dirt bike\r\n\r\nriders with a world-class trail system. All trails are open 365 days a year and new trails are\r\n\r\nconstantly being added.\r\n\r\n28 Big Pinnacle Branch Rd.\r\n\r\nJulian, WV 25529\r\n\r\nwww.trailsheaven.com\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\neNeRGy Rock Climbing Gym\r\n\r\nIndoor Rock Climbing Gym providing opportunities for beginners through experts to climb in the\r\n\r\nCharleston area. The gym features 16 ft tall 5, 10 and 15 degree overhanging walls, 14 ft tall 30\r\n\r\ndegree overhanging wall, a cave with 45, 60 and horizontal roof features/. The cave also has a\r\n\r\n14 ft long hand crack that splits and an overhanging arete. In the loft area, there is a 13 ft tall 50\r\n\r\ndegree wall that is perfect for training. There is also a 13 ft tall \'wave\' wall for transitional angle\r\n\r\ntraining and a mushroom wall to practice mantling and topping out. Shoes available for rental\r\n\r\nand day passes (5-9pm) available for $12. No additional equipment needed prior to entry.\r\n\r\n269 Graham Dr.\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25302\r\n\r\nhttp://www.energyrockgym.com/\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nHidden Trails Motorsports\r\n\r\nHidden Trails Motorsports sell new and used motorsports vehicles with brands including Can-\r\n\r\nAm, Sea-Doo, Spyder, Suzuki and all Yamaha brands. They also service and have part\r\n\r\navailable for the brands listed as well as powersports brands including Polaris, Kawasaki, Arctic\r\n\r\ncat and Honda.\r\n\r\n3014 E Dupont Ave.\r\n\r\nBelle, WV 25015\r\n\r\nhttp://www.hiddentrailsmoto.com/\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nBridgeWalk\r\n\r\nTake a walk along the bottom of the New River Gorge Bridge! This 2-3 hour tour will take guests\r\n\r\nfrom the Canyon Rim Visitor Center across the 3030 foot length of the bridge and then shuttle\r\n\r\nback to the center. The catwalk has been an existing structure of the bridge since its original\r\n\r\nconstruction, and Bridge Walk LLC saw an opportunity to give unique tours across the walkway.\r\n\r\nCreating Bridge Walk only required a simple shuttle system, improving the trail access, and\r\n\r\ninstalling an innovative safety system for guests making it impossible for tour guests to fall off\r\n\r\nthe bridge.\r\n\r\nCanyon Rim Visitor Center\r\n\r\n162 Visitor Center Rd.\r\n\r\nLansing, WV 25862\r\n\r\nhttp://bridgewalk.com/\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nBest Events for Adrenaline Junkies\r\n\r\nWV Games/Sportsfest\r\n\r\nCome out and enjoy jet ski racing, professional volleyball and tons more during this fun-filled\r\n\r\nweekend. The \"Governors\' Cup\" is the final stop of the Hydro-Turf Pro Watercross Tour, where\r\n\r\nthe pro riders who have been traveling the tour will be crowned the U.S.A. National Champions.\r\n\r\nAmateur, Novice and Junior competitors will also be vying for the National Amateur\r\n\r\nChampionship title. For more information on the National Championship Pro Watercross Tour.\r\n\r\nBridge Day\r\n\r\nBridge Day, one of the largest extreme sports event in the world, is held annually on the third\r\n\r\nSaturday in October in Fayette County, West Virginia (WV). Hundreds of BASE jumpers and\r\n\r\nnearly 80,000 spectators are expected to attend the event. Vendor booths and food are\r\n\r\navailable on the bridge, along with the best overlook of the New River Gorge.\r\n\r\n  \r\n\r\nBest Time of the Year\r\n\r\nFall is a great time to catch some great (and unique) events for adrenaline junkies.  September\r\n\r\nand October offer good weather but not hot conditions.',	'Adrenaline Junkie',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'206-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-06-29 10:11:33',	'2015-06-29 14:11:33',	'',	206,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/206-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
