ersports brands including Polaris, Kawasaki, Arctic Cat and Honda.\r\n3014 E Dupont Ave.\r\nBelle, WV 25015\r\nhttp://www.hiddentrailsmoto.com/\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>BridgeWalk</h3>\r\nTake a walk along the bottom of the New River Gorge Bridge! This 2-3 hour tour will take guests from the Canyon Rim Visitor Center across the 3030 foot length of the bridge and then shuttle\r\nback to the center. The catwalk has been an existing structure of the bridge since its original construction, and Bridge Walk LLC saw an opportunity to give unique tours across the walkway.\r\nCreating Bridge Walk only required a simple shuttle system, improving the trail access, and installing an innovative safety system for guests making it impossible for tour guests to fall off the bridge.\r\nCanyon Rim Visitor Center\r\n162 Visitor Center Rd.\r\nLansing, WV 25862\r\nhttp://bridgewalk.com/\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nBest Events for Adrenaline Junkies\r\n\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-240 alignleft\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/volleyball4-300x177.jpg\" alt=\"volleyball4\" width=\"170\" height=\"100\" />\r\n<h3>WV Games/Sportsfest</h3>\r\nCome out and enjoy jet ski racing, professional volleyball and tons more during this fun-filled weekend. The \"Governors\' Cup\" is the final stop of the Hydro-Turf Pro Watercross Tour, where\r\nthe pro riders who have been traveling the tour will be crowned the U.S.A. National Champions. Amateur, Novice and Junior competitors will also be vying for the National Amateur Championship title. For more information on the National Championship Pro Watercross Tour.\r\n<h3>Bridge Day</h3>\r\nBridge Day, one of the largest extreme sports event in the world, is held annually on the third Saturday in October in Fayette County, West Virginia (WV). Hundreds of BASE jumpers and nearly 80,000 spectators are expected to attend the event. Vendor booths and food are available on the bridge, along with the best overlook of the New River Gorge.\r\n\r\n  