(267,	3,	'2015-06-29 14:28:33',	'2015-06-29 18:28:33',	'<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/FestivALL_2014_Childrens_Art_Fair_11_SMALLER_Sava_-__Javins_authorized.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-253\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/FestivALL_2014_Childrens_Art_Fair_11_SMALLER_Sava_-__Javins_authorized-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"FestivALL_2014_Childrens_Art_Fair_11_SMALLER_Sava_-__Javins_authorized\" width=\"170\" height=\"113\" /></a><\r\n<h2 class=\"content-block\">Charleston is a great place for families!  With so many exciting kid-friendly activities including sports, arts and food, theres never a dull moment. For more ideas for family fun, check out our event calendar.</h2>\r\n<h3>WV Power</h3>\r\nMinor League baseball team in the South Atlantic League. The Class A Pittsburgh Pirates affiliate plays home games at Appalachian Power Park, also home to the WVSSAC baseball tournament.\r\nAppalachian Power Park\r\n601 Morris St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\nwvpower.com\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Public Libraries</h3>\r\nOur local libraries are great places for fun and learning! Many events, programs &amp; services are free to the public. Kanawha County public library also provides geocaching equipment for rent.\r\n<h3>Kanawha County Public Library</h3>\r\n123 Capitol St\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\nhttp://kanawhalibrary.org/\r\n<h3>South Charleston Public Library</h3>\r\n312 4th Avenue\r\nSouth Charleston WV 25303\r\nhttp://www.southcharlestonlibrary.org/\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nChuck E Cheese\r\n\r\nLocated at Southridge Centre, Chuck E. Cheeses is a kid-centric experience. Admission is free and games require tokens that can be purchased. There\'s also a show consisting of characters &amp; music.\r\n\r\n2846 Mountaineer Blvd.\r\nCharleston, WV, 25309\r\nhttp://www.chuckecheese.com/\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWaterways\r\n\r\nWaterways offers pool, tube &amp; body slides, lazy river, walking trail, unlimited putt-putt golf and kiddie island. Shelters available for family outings. Concession food is available for meals and snacks.\r\n\r\n109 Water Way\r\nAlkol, WV 25501\r\nhttp://waterwayspark.net/\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nClay Center for the Arts and Sciences\r\n\r\nA 240,000 sq ft structure housing performing &amp; visual arts and sciences under one roof. Home to the Avampato Discovery Museum, Juliet Museum of Art and Maier Foundation Performance\r\nHall.\r\n\r\nOne Clay Square\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\nhttp://www.theclaycenter.org/\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThe Peanut Shoppe\r\n\r\nThe Peanut Shoppe has been a Charleston tradition for over 60 years. Established in 1950 by Delbert Moore, it is still in its original location. We recommend the chocolate stars!\r\n\r\n126 Capitol St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\nhttps://www.facebook.com/thepeanutshoppe\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCamden Park\r\n\r\nLooking for old-fashioned fun? Camden Park, WVs only amusement park, is a 26 acre park located near Huntington. Established in 1903, the park is home to more than thirty rides and\r\nattractions, including a full-size traditional wooden roller coaster and several other vintage rides.\r\n\r\n5000 Waverly Rd.\r\nHuntington, WV 25704\r\nwww.camdenpark.com/\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCoonskin Park\r\n\r\nThe park includes over 1,000 acres of hiking/biking trails, an accessible 18 hole golf course, Olympic size pool, picnic shelters, tennis courts, horseshoe pits, playground, ampitheater,\r\nsoccer stadium and wedding garden.\r\n\r\n2000 Coonskin Drive\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\nhttp://www.kcprc.com/Parks/Coonskin-Park.aspx\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nBest Events for Families\r\n\r\nPhoto attached - Festivall\r\n\r\nClay Center Family Fun Days\r\nEach day is full of family entertainment with themed science and art activities taking place throughout the day in addition to our three floors of art and science exhibits.\r\n\r\nChildren\'s Art Fair and Kanawha County Public Library Street Fair\r\n\r\nA perfect combination for two days of family fun: Make &amp; take craft opportunities from invited artisans and groups, a sale of work by children and youth in Kanawha County neighborhood programs; a stage with child-friendly performances\r\n\r\nMovie Nights at Magic Island\r\n\r\nSponsored by local radio station, WQBE, Magic Island becomes a free, family friendly movie theater under the stars. The Island opens up at 6 with a Kids Zone &amp; the movie will start around dusk! Movie Nights take place Wednesday nights in June.\r\n\r\n  \r\n\r\nBest Time of the Year\r\n\r\nAll year long there\'s plenty of Family Fun in Charleston, WV!',	'Family Fun',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'202-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-06-29 14:28:33',	'2015-06-29 18:28:33',	'',	202,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/202-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
