(288,	3,	'2015-06-30 08:12:22',	'2015-06-30 12:12:22',	'Charlestons diverse opportunities for entertainment, fun and learning makes it a great place to\r\n\r\nvisit and to live! Heres a few ideas for the city explorer in all of us.\r\n\r\nClay Center for the Arts and Sciences\r\n\r\nA 240,000 sq ft structure housing performing &amp; visual arts and sciences under one roof. Home\r\n\r\nto the Avampato Discovery Museum, Juliet Museum of Art and Maier Foundation Performance\r\n\r\nHall.\r\n\r\nOne Clay Square\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n\r\nhttp://www.theclaycenter.org/<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/festivall_pic.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-287\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/festivall_pic-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"festivall_pic\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCapitol Street\r\n\r\nThis bustling street serves as a main location for dining, learning and retail. Restaurants such as\r\n\r\nIchiban, Pies and Pints, Adelphia, Graziano\'s Pizza and others line the streets, some offering\r\n\r\noutdoor dining.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nArtWalk\r\n\r\nA free self-guided walking tour of Downtown Charleston\'s shops, galleries and businesses\r\n\r\nfeaturing a variety of art - from paintings and sculptures to photography and music. ArtWalk is\r\n\r\nheld the third Thursday of each month.\r\n\r\nhttp://www.artwalkcwv.com/\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCapitol Market\r\n\r\nBuilt from an 1800s railroad transfer dock, the market serves as an indoor/outdoor farmer\'s\r\n\r\nmarket, home of a variety of specialty shops and Sohos restaurant. The Charleston CVB also\r\n\r\nhas a satellite site at the market.\r\n\r\n800 Smith Street\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n\r\nhttp://www.capitolmarket.net/\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nLive on the Levee\r\n\r\nAn outdoor concert series presented by the City of Charleston, WV. The concerts take place\r\n\r\neach Friday from Memorial Day Weekend to Labor Day Weekend.\r\n\r\nKanawha Blvd.\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n\r\nliveontheleveecharleston.com\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nBridge Road Shops\r\n\r\nUnique shops located in a charming neighborhood commercial district. Experience world class\r\n\r\ndining, shop for your favorite designer clothes, decorate your home with the warmth of one-of-a\r\n\r\nkind accessories, and experience local and regional art.\r\n\r\nwww.bridgeroad.org\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nHale Street\r\n\r\nThis hidden street gem offers a unique group of stores and restaurants. Shop at Stray Dog\r\n\r\nAntiques, get pampered at Tops Off Barber Shop, Salon and Spa, get a smoothie at Mission\r\n\r\nSavvy Vegan Cafe and dinner at Celsius.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nBest Events\r\n\r\nFestivAll\r\n\r\nThe event features visual arts, music, theater, dance and film as well as other cultural and\r\n\r\nentertainment events. It mixes fine arts and pop arts in venues and locations all over Charleston\r\n\r\nand includes a wide variety of styles and genres.\r\n\r\n  \r\n\r\nBest Time of the Year\r\n\r\nAll year long Charleston has lots to offer the City Explorer. There\'s always something to do in\r\n\r\nthe area!',	'City Explorer',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'187-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-06-30 08:12:22',	'2015-06-30 12:12:22',	'',	187,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/187-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(289,	3,	'2015-06-30 08:18:11',	'2015-06-30 12:18:11',	'The beer is flowing in the capitol city. With new laws in WV allowing growlers to be purchased\r\n\r\nat Charleston establishments and bars, the craft beer craze is even stronger in the Mountain\r\n\r\nState.\r\n\r\nCharleston Brewing Company\r\n\r\nA micro-brewery attached to Black Sheep Burritos in the heart of downtown Charleston. Fine\r\n\r\ncraft beers of all styles brewed and served on-site.\r\n\r\n702 Quarrier St,\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n\r\nwww.charlestonbrewingcompany.com\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nPies and Pints\r\n\r\nPies &amp; Pints restaurant in Charleston West Virginia serves unique, delicious gourmet pizza and\r\n\r\ncraft beer in the center of the city\'s downtown shopping district.\r\n\r\n222 Capitol Street\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n\r\nhttp://piesandpints.net/\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nBricks and Barrels\r\n\r\nIf you\'re looking for something different, Bricks and Barrels is a great option! Sit in one of the\r\n\r\nBarrel shaped booths and enjoy their large variety of beers and wines and food from their\r\n\r\neclectic menu.\r\n\r\n1214 Smith St.\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n\r\nhttp://www.bricksnbarrels.com/\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThe Wine &amp; Cheese Shop\r\n\r\nLocated at the Capitol Market, the shop features a huge selection of wine, cheese, craft beer,\r\n\r\ngift items, accessories, and glassware.\r\n\r\n800 Smith Street\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n\r\nhttp://www.capitolmarket.net/merchants/wine-cheese-shop\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nB&amp;D Gastropub\r\n\r\nThe extensive menu includes appetizers such as jerk chicken nachos &amp; feta and dates wrapped\r\n\r\nin bacon. The menu will also offers burgers, including stuffed patties, fresh-cut chips and salads.\r\n\r\n200 35th St SE #1\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25304\r\n\r\nwww.facebook.com/BandDGastropub\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCopper Pint Pub\r\n\r\nCopper Pint Pub is an Irish Pub with a large selection of local and imported craft beers. Also\r\n\r\ncarry a huge selection of Irish Whiskeys, Bourbons and Scotches to satisfy the most diverse\r\n\r\ntaste buds.\r\n\r\n808 Kanawha Blvd., E\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n\r\nhttps://www.facebook.com/CopperPintPub\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nBest Events\r\n\r\nFest of Ale\r\n\r\nThe Charleston area\'s original beer tasting event. Held at the Comedy Zone, participants\r\n\r\nsample 10-12 beers along with food pairings. Entertainment provided by the Comedy Zone.\r\n\r\nSome wine offerings are available in place of beer for those who want to try something different.\r\n\r\nBlues, Brews and BBQ\r\n\r\nPart of FestivAll, Charlestons Fund for the Arts produces this day long concert and lawn party.\r\n\r\nBeer and BBQ vendors provide suds and great food while blues musicians take the stage and\r\n\r\nattendees enjoy the lawn of the University of Charleston.\r\n\r\n  \r\n\r\nBest Time of the Year\r\n\r\nFall is a great time for beer tastings and other events that celebrate the brew...plus Oktoberfest\r\n\r\nbeers are coming out! Enjoy beer year-round at local restaurants as well.',	'Brew Enthusiast',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'198-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-06-30 08:18:11',	'2015-06-30 12:18:11',	'',	198,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/198-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(290,	3,	'2015-06-30 08:22:44',	'2015-06-30 12:22:44',	'FOODIE\r\n\r\nYou dont have to look very far to find great cuisine in Charleston! We have highlighted just a\r\n\r\nfew of the amazing places you can go to have a casual meal, a quick bite, a fancy feast or make\r\n\r\nyour own!\r\n\r\nBluegrass Kitchen\r\n\r\nFarm-to-table comfort food with a modern edge. Specialties are vegetarian &amp; omnivorous dishes\r\n\r\nmade from ingredients naturally sourced within WV and the Appalachians served in a dining\r\n\r\nroom restored to its circa 1920\'s beauty.\r\n\r\n1600 Washington St E\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\n\r\nwww.bluegrasswv.com/\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCharleston Bread Company\r\n\r\nBreads, cookies, pastries and more baked fresh every day.\r\n\r\n601 Capitol St.\r\n\r\nCharleston, West Virginia 25301\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThe Block\r\n\r\nThe Block offers cocktails and small bites complimented by views of downtown Capitol St. The\r\n\r\nrestaurant features an active cheese cave and glass enclosed wine cellar. Jazz music on\r\n\r\nselected nights.\r\n\r\n201 Capitol St.\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n\r\nwww.theblockwv.com/\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCapitol Market\r\n\r\nBuilt from an 1800s railroad transfer dock, the market serves as an indoor/outdoor farmer\'s\r\n\r\nmarket, home of a variety of specialty shops and Sohos restaurant. The Charleston CVB also\r\n\r\nhas a satellite site at the market.\r\n\r\n800 Smith Street\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n\r\nhttp://www.capitolmarket.net/\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nJ.Q. Dickenson Salt Works\r\n\r\nDescendants of the original salt makers in the Kanawha Valley produce clean, artisinal salt,\r\n\r\nharvested by hand. Tours are available with reservations.\r\n\r\n371 Kanawha Salines Dr.\r\n\r\nMalden, WV 25306\r\n\r\nwww.jqdsalt.com/\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nBlack Sheep Burritos\r\n\r\nLocated in the heart of downtown, Black Sheep offers an eclectic mix of tex-mex menu items\r\n\r\nand Charleston Brewing Company beer. One of the best brunch menus in the Kanawha Valley.\r\n\r\n702 Quarrier St,\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n\r\nwww.blacksheepwv.com/\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nEllens Ice Cream\r\n\r\nEllens Homemade Ice Cream was born over 15 years ago with the simple mission to delight\r\n\r\ncustomers with all-natural, high-quality ingredients and a welcoming and comfortable\r\n\r\natmosphere.\r\n\r\n225 Capitol St,\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n\r\nhttp://ellensicecream.com/\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWest Side Farmers Market\r\n\r\nThe purpose and mission of the market is to educate about local food resources and to\r\n\r\nrevitalize the community by creating a vibrant market at which local farmers and home\r\n\r\ngardeners may sell their produce.\r\n\r\n303 Washington St. West\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25302\r\n\r\nhttp://wsfmcharleston.com/\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nButter It Up!\r\n\r\nEver had butter in your coffee? This is a must-try. Butter it up! is a gluten free coffee shop.\r\n\r\nThey offer paleoish breakfast, lunch, and dinner options in addition to local products.\r\n\r\n714 Virginia St E,\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n\r\nhttps://www.facebook.com/butteritupcrw\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nBest Events\r\n\r\nSmoke on the Water Chili Cookoff\r\n\r\nChili cooks compete to see who has the best red, green and home-style chili and salsa. Kids\r\n\r\nactivities, frozen t-shirt and hot pepper eating contests, live music, local food vendors and plenty\r\n\r\nof cold drinks. Proceeds benefit HospiceCare.\r\n\r\nMac and Cheese Cookoff\r\n\r\nMac and Cheese enthusiasts enter and taste the Charleston area\'s best Macaroni and Cheese.\r\n\r\nProceeds benefit the Childhood Language Center of Charleston, WV.\r\n\r\nTaste-of-All\r\n\r\nTaste-of-All Charleston is a tour of the culinary talents and amazing cuisine available throughout\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV. Fun for the whole family, visitors can taste amazing dishes served by some of\r\n\r\nthe gifted chefs and restaurants from the valley.\r\n\r\n  \r\n\r\nBest Time of the Year\r\n\r\nSpring, summer and fall are perfect for outdoor dining but all year-round is great for those\r\n\r\nspecial Charleston places that love to serve you!',	'Foodie',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'189-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-06-30 08:22:44',	'2015-06-30 12:22:44',	'',	189,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/189-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(291,	3,	'2015-06-30 08:23:31',	'2015-06-30 12:23:31',	'HISTORY BUFF\r\n\r\nCharlestons diverse opportunities for entertainment, fun and learning makes it a great place to\r\n\r\nvisit and to live! Heres a few ideas for the city explorer in all of us.\r\n\r\nWV State Museum\r\n\r\nThis free-to-the-pubic museum offers an interactive look into the history, culture and treasures\r\n\r\nof West Virginia. The museum is designed as a timeline telling story of WV. A museum gift shop\r\n\r\noffers WV locally-made products.\r\n\r\nWV Division of Culture and History\r\n\r\nCapitol Complex\r\n\r\n1900 Kanawha Boulevard East\r\n\r\nCharleston WV 25305\r\n\r\nhttp://www.wvculture.org/museum/State-Museum-Index.html\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWV Humanities Council\r\n\r\nThe Council provides constant events and programs promoting the Mountain State and it\'s art,\r\n\r\nliterature and history. It is located at the MacFarland-Hubbard House, which is listed on the\r\n\r\nNational Register of Historic Places.\r\n\r\n1310 Kanawha Blvd., E.\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n\r\nhttp://www.wvhumanities.org/\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nMalden\r\n\r\nHistoric town just east of Charleston. VIsit Booker T. Washington\'s childhood home, African Zion\r\n\r\nBasptist Church, J.Q. Dickenson Salt and many other historic buildings and sites.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nGovernors Mansion\r\n\r\nTours of the Governor\'s Mansion begin on the front porch of the Mansion on Thursdays and\r\n\r\nFridays. Reservations are required and are honored on a first-come, first-serve basis. Call for\r\n\r\nreservations at 304-558-4839.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWest Virginia State Capitol\r\n\r\nTours begin on the first floor Rotunda. Groups under 10 are welcome to join a regularly\r\n\r\nscheduled tour without reservations. Groups of more than 10 are best served with a reservation\r\n\r\nand tours of Senate/Representatives chamber require reservations. 304-558-2601\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCraik-Patton House\r\n\r\nCraik-Patton House was built about 1834 in the Greek Revival style. It is open for tours from\r\n\r\nApril through October. It is listed on the National Register of Historic Places since 1970.\r\n\r\n2809 Kanawha Blvd. E.\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\n\r\nhttp://www.craik-patton.org/\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCoal Heritage Trail\r\n\r\nA driving trail that winds through over 187 rugged miles of scenic industrial heritage. You will\r\n\r\npass through National Historic Districts and the physical remnants of the coal boom such as\r\n\r\ncoal miners\' homes, company stores, company offices and more.\r\n\r\n100 Kelly Avenue\r\n\r\nOak Hill, WEST VIRGINIA 25901\r\n\r\nwww.coalheritage.org\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nBlenko Glass\r\n\r\nFor over 100 years, Blenko has maintained the tradition of hand making glassware in America.\r\n\r\nThey offer a wide range of products which include functional glassware, art glass, mouth blown\r\n\r\nsheet glass, dalle de verre and other quality products. Tours are available.\r\n\r\n9 Bill Blenko Drive\r\n\r\nMilton, WV 25541\r\n\r\nhttp://www.blenko.com/\r\n\r\nKanawha Blvd. Historical Markers\r\n\r\nAs you stroll along the riverbank, you will come across a series of historic markers\r\n\r\ncommemorating moments in West Virginia history. These markers are part of the over 1,000\r\n\r\nmarkers throughout the state marking sites of significance.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nBest Events\r\n\r\nBattle of Scary Creek/Skirmish at Hurricane Bridge - Civil War Reenactment\r\n\r\nPart of a Civil War weekend in Hurricane, the event commemorates two engagements of the\r\n\r\nCivil War separated by a space of two years. The Battle of Scary Creek., July 17, 1861 and the\r\n\r\nBlue and Gray Skirmish at Hurricane Bridge, March 28, 1863. Also, enjoy crafts, sutler\'s row,\r\n\r\nstorytelling, a night firing, parade drills, a ladies tea, a historical lantern tour and a military\r\n\r\ndance.\r\n\r\nWV Day Celebrations\r\n\r\nCelebrate West Virginia\'s birthday with a variety of activities on the grounds of the WV State\r\n\r\nCapitol.\r\n\r\n  \r\n\r\nBest Time of the Year\r\n\r\nHistory is happening every day of the year and this is certainly the case for those wanting to learn\r\n\r\nmore about Charleston and West Virginia\'s history.',	'History Buff',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'191-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-06-30 08:23:31',	'2015-06-30 12:23:31',	'',	191,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/191-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(292,	3,	'2015-06-30 08:25:01',	'2015-06-30 12:25:01',	'MUSIC LOVER\r\n\r\nThe music of the Charleston area is a diverse and eclectic mix, sure to please the ears of all\r\n\r\nlooking for some great tunes. Live performances are abundant in the area at small and large\r\n\r\nvenues as well as a variety of special events.\r\n\r\nEmpty Glass\r\n\r\nLocated under a 3-story house jacked up in the air in Charlestons historically diverse East End.\r\n\r\nHere you will find delicious food, great conversation, friendly spirits and live original music from\r\n\r\nall over the planet.\r\n\r\n410 Elizabeth St.\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\n\r\nwww.emptyglass.com\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nMountain Stage\r\n\r\nFor over 30 years \"Mountain Stage w/ Larry Groce\" has been the home of live music on public\r\n\r\nradio. Founded in 1983 in Charleston, WV and is produced by West Virginia Public Radio the\r\n\r\nshow travels but most are recorded at the WV State Capitol Complex.\r\n\r\nCulture Center Theater\r\n\r\nCapitol Complex\r\n\r\n1900 Kanawha Boulevard East\r\n\r\nCharleston WV 25305\r\n\r\nwww.mountainstage.org\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nTaylor Books\r\n\r\nIn addition to an open mic night and scheduled performances, they have a broad selection of\r\n\r\nbooks, wide variety of hard-to-find magazines and unique collection of cards and gifts as well as\r\n\r\nan Art Annex.\r\n\r\n226 Capitol St.\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n\r\nwww.taylorbooks.com\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWV Symphony Orchestra\r\n\r\nThe West Virginia Symphony Orchestra presents classical, pops, family &amp; chamber-music\r\n\r\nconcerts annually. The WVSO also provides affordable, high-quality concerts, collaborations\r\n\r\nwith arts organizations and a nationally award-winning education program.\r\n\r\nOne Clay Square\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n\r\nwvsymphony.org\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nLive on the Levee\r\n\r\nAn outdoor concert series presented by the City of Charleston, WV. The concerts take place\r\n\r\neach Friday from Memorial Day Weekend to Labor Day Weekend.\r\n\r\nKanawha Blvd.\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n\r\nliveontheleveecharleston.com\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nBrown Bag Concerts\r\n\r\nFree Lunchtime Concerts in Davis Park the third Wednesday of the month from May until\r\n\r\nSeptember. The concerts last from 11:30am to 1:30pm.\r\n\r\nDavis Park\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nFret and Fiddle\r\n\r\nFret \'n Fiddle offers new and used string instruments. Specializing in vintage instruments,\r\n\r\nincluding guitars, mandolins, banjos and fiddles. They also offer consigned merchandise and a\r\n\r\nrecording studio.\r\n\r\n809 Pennsylvania Ave.\r\n\r\nSt Albans, WV 25177\r\n\r\nwww.fretnfiddle.com\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSullivan\'s Records\r\n\r\nCharleston\'s newest record store! They specialize in vinyl, with thousands of new &amp; used\r\n\r\nrecords in stock, as well as tons of CD\'s, DVD\'s, and more.\r\n\r\n1588-A Washington St E,\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\n\r\nhttp://sullivansrecords.com/\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWV Music Hall of Fame\r\n\r\nThe WV Music Hall of Fame has a satellite exhibit in the Dickinson Street parking. The display\r\n\r\nfeatures instruments, photos, posters and vintage memorabilia from Mountain Stage musicians\r\n\r\n with an emphasis on those from the Kanawha Valley.\r\n\r\nQuarrier and Dickenson Sts.\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n\r\nhttp://www.wvmusichalloffame.com/\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nBest Events\r\n\r\nVandalia Gathering\r\n\r\nThe Vandalia Gathering brings together the finest traditional Appalachian musicians for a\r\n\r\nweekend of great picking. Elder statesmen and young upstarts perform on stage, compete in\r\n\r\ncontests and play in impromptu jam sessions all over the Capitol Complex. Visitors to the\r\n\r\nGathering can enjoy fiddle, banjo, mandolin and guitar contests outside during the day, and\r\n\r\nconcerts in the State Theater in the evenings. Food and craft vendors are also part of the\r\n\r\nfestival.\r\n\r\nSymphony Sunday\r\n\r\nFree day of music with the WV Symphony Orchestra and other musicians on the lawn of the\r\n\r\nUniversity of Charleston. Artisan tents and food vendors are also present throughout the day.\r\n\r\nThe day ends with the Symphony playing and fireworks.\r\n\r\nWine &amp; All That Jazz Festival\r\n\r\nPart of FestivAll, Charlestons Fund for the Arts produces this day long concert and lawn party.\r\n\r\nWest Virginia wineries sell glasses and bottles of a variety of wines, jazz musicians take the\r\n\r\nstage and attendees enjoy the lawn of the University of Charleston.\r\n\r\n  \r\n\r\nBest Time of the Year\r\n\r\nSummer is a music lover\'s paradise in the Charleston area. With a large variety of outdoor\r\n\r\nconcerts and events, there\'s always an opportunity to enjoy the sweet sounds of summer in\r\n\r\nCharlie West.',	'Music Lover',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'196-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-06-30 08:25:01',	'2015-06-30 12:25:01',	'',	196,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/196-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
