(295,	3,	'2015-06-30 08:28:33',	'2015-06-30 12:28:33',	'NIGHT OWL\r\n\r\nWhether you want fast-paced excitement, great music or a low-key culinary experience, theres\r\n\r\nalways something to do late-night in Charleston!\r\n\r\nComedy Zone\r\n\r\nTwo of the nation\'s funniest comedians travel to Charleston to entertain the crowds. Full food\r\n\r\nand drink menus available during the show. Shows are Fridays at 8pm &amp; Saturdays at 7pm and\r\n\r\n9pm.\r\n\r\n400 2nd Ave.\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25303\r\n\r\ncomedyzonecharleston.com\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCapitol Street Nightlife\r\n\r\nCapitol Street &amp; adjacent Kanawha Blvd. have a variety of bars/lounges for all scenes. Whether\r\n\r\nyoure looking for a great glass of wine, sports bar, irish pub or game of pool, its all here!\r\n\r\nCapitol St.\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nBricks and Barrels\r\n\r\nIf you\'re looking for an upscale evening, Bricks and Barrels is the place. Sit in one of the Barrel\r\n\r\nshaped booths and enjoy their large variety of beers and wines along with their eclectic menu.\r\n\r\n1214 Smith St.\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n\r\nhttp://www.bricksnbarrels.com/\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nEmpty Glass\r\n\r\nLocated under a 3-story house jacked up in the air in Charlestons historically diverse East End.\r\n\r\nHere you will find delicious food, great conversation, friendly spirits and live original music.\r\n\r\n410 Elizabeth St.\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\n\r\nwww.emptyglass.com\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCelsius\r\n\r\nAn upscale lounge serving wine, craft beers and specialty cocktails. The food menu includes\r\n\r\nburgers, salads, flat breads and a unique variety of dishes.\r\n\r\n212 Hale St\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n\r\nhttps://www.facebook.com/CelsiusWV\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nTimothy\'s\r\n\r\nTimothys is located directly below the Quarrier Diner. Watch your favorite sports on any one of\r\n\r\nthe 17 high definition flat screens. They are constantly hosting events from live music, trivia\r\n\r\nnights and more.\r\n\r\n1022 Quarrier St.\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n\r\nhttp://www.timothyssportsbar.com/\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nMardi Gras Casino\r\n\r\nOver 90,000 square feet of gaming space, the Mardi Gras Casino offers over 30 table games,\r\n\r\nover 1,000 slot machines, greyhound racing, restaurants and bars and much more!\r\n\r\n#1 Greyhound Drive\r\n\r\nCross Lanes, WV 25313\r\n\r\nhttp://www.mardigrascasinowv.com/\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nBest Events\r\n\r\n.\r\n\r\nLive On The Levee\r\n\r\nOutdoor concert series presented by the City of Charleston, WV. The concerts take place each\r\n\r\nFriday from Memorial Day Weekend to Labor Day Weekend.\r\n\r\nEast End Pub Crawl\r\n\r\nJoin in on the St. Patrick\'s Day fun on the East End of Charleston.  Live, local Celtic music from\r\n\r\nFOOTMAD, walk from bar to bar (over 10) enjoying drink specials and look for the hidden\r\n\r\nshamrocks throughout the area in order to win big!\r\n\r\nBoo Bash\r\n\r\nAll the ghosts and goblins come out to play at this traditional-style Halloween party.  dance the\r\n\r\nnight away with the event\'s DJ and enjoy great food and drinks, games and a photo booth.\r\n\r\nHosted by the South Charleston Chamber of Commerce, its a fun-filled fright night!\r\n\r\nHallowEast<img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-294\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/live_on_levee1-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"live_on_levee1\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nIf you\'re looking for a spooky time, HallowEast has lots of events to make your Halloween.\r\n\r\nArtMares, Main Street Murder Mystery, East End Zombie Walk, Run Like Hell Zombie 5K and\r\n\r\nthe Costume Crawl are all exciting events that make this week of scary a truly ghouly\r\n\r\nexperience.\r\n\r\nMurder Mysteries\r\n\r\nThese exciting Who-Dun-It events are sure to entertain the best of detectives.  Located at the\r\n\r\nComedy Zone in the Holiday Inn &amp; Suites, participants enjoy a buffet dinner and an entertaining\r\n\r\ninteractive show with a different theme each time.\r\n\r\n  \r\n\r\nBest Time of the Year\r\n\r\nThere\'s always time to party!  But if you\'re looking for great times with special events, look\r\n\r\naround the holidays...particularly St. Patty\'s Day and Halloween!<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/murder.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-293\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/murder-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"murder\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a>',	'Night Owl',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'200-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-06-30 08:28:33',	'2015-06-30 12:28:33',	'',	200,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/200-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(296,	3,	'2015-06-30 08:30:35',	'2015-06-30 12:30:35',	'Sport Fan\r\n\r\nTheres a lot of great competition in Charleston! Whether youre a spectator or a competitor,\r\n\r\ncheck out these great opportunities in all kinds of different sports.\r\n\r\nWV Power\r\n\r\nMinor League baseball team in the South Atlantic League. The Class A Pittsburgh Pirates\r\n\r\naffiliate plays home games at Appalachian Power Park, also home to the WVSSAC baseball\r\n\r\ntournament.\r\n\r\nAppalachian Power Park\r\n\r\n601 Morris St.\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n\r\nwvpower.com\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWV Chaos\r\n\r\nFounded in 2003, WV Chaos plays in the USL Premier Development League (PDL), the 4th tier\r\n\r\nof the American Soccer Pyramid, in the South Atlantic Division of the Eastern Conference.\r\n\r\nSchoenbaum Soccer Complex\r\n\r\n2000 Coonskin Dr.\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\n\r\nwestvirginiachaossoccer.com\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nUniversity of Charleston Athletics\r\n\r\nThe UC Golden Eagles teams consist of baseball, basketball, cross country, football, golf\r\n\r\n,soccer, tennis, track and field, volleyball, cheerleading, rowing, lacrosse and softball.\r\n\r\nUniversity of Charleston\r\n\r\n2300 MacCorkle Ave., SE\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25304\r\n\r\nUC Stadium - Laidley Field\r\n\r\n200 Elizabeth St.\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\n\r\nucgoldeneagles.com\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWest Virginia State University Athletics\r\n\r\nThe WVSU Yellow Jackets teams consist of baseball, basketball, football, golf, tennis, softball,\r\n\r\ncross country and volleyball.\r\n\r\n500 Fairlawn Ave.\r\n\r\nInstitute, WV 25112\r\n\r\nwww.wvsuyellowjackets.com\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCharleston Civic Center\r\n\r\nHosts a variety of annual sporting events including WVSSAC Boys and Girls Basketball State\r\n\r\nTournaments, archery and volleyball tournaments, Mountain East Conference Championships,\r\n\r\nboxing/martial arts events, Capital Classic between WVU and Marshall Men\'s Basketball.\r\n\r\n200 Civic Center Dr.\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n\r\nwww.charlestonwvciviccenter.com\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nTrace Fork Soccer Complex\r\n\r\nThe Friends of Coal Fields At Trace Fork Soccer Complex is a six field soccer complex is\r\n\r\nlocated at the Shops at Trace Fork, just off U.S. Rt. 119 south of Charleston, West Virginia.\r\n\r\n25 RHL Blvd.\r\n\r\nSouth Charleston, WV 25309\r\n\r\nhttp://traceforksoccer.com/\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nAdelphia Sports Bar and Grille\r\n\r\nVoted best appetizer and wings in the valley three years in a row! Adelphia infuses Greek and\r\n\r\nAmerican cuisine to offer some of the best food around. Open 365 days a year and full menu\r\n\r\nserved until midnight and later.\r\n\r\n218 Capitol Street\r\n\r\nCharleston WV, 25301\r\n\r\nhttp://adelphiasportsbar.com/\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSouth Charleston Memorial Ice Arena\r\n\r\nNewly opened, state-of-the-art facility with amenities like an arcade and heated seating area\r\n\r\nthat will accommodate 500 spectators. Groups of all sizes are welcome.\r\n\r\n20 RHL Blvd.\r\n\r\nCharleston, WV 25309\r\n\r\nhttp://cityofsouthcharleston.com/memorial-ice-arena/\r\n\r\nLittle Creek Park\r\n\r\nThe park has five baseball/softball fields, seven soccer fields, a football field, two tennis courts\r\n\r\nand two basketball courts. Also, 18-hold disc golf course and soap box derby track are located\r\n\r\nat the park.\r\n\r\n1 Little Creek Park Rd.\r\n\r\nSouth Charleston, WV 25309\r\n\r\nhttp://cityofsouthcharleston.com/little-creek-park/\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nBest Events\r\n\r\nAnnual Charleston Public Courts Tennis Tournament\r\n\r\nJuly 10-18, 2015\r\n\r\nLargest annual tennis tournament in Charleston. The public courts tournament matches take\r\n\r\nplace at Schoenbaum Tennis Complex, Tennis Indoor Center and Charleston Catholic High\r\n\r\nSchool Sports Complex. rain sites include tennis indoor center, YMCA and the Charleston\r\n\r\nTennis Club.\r\n\r\nWVSSAC Tournaments\r\n\r\nThe West Virginia Secondary School Athletic Commission (WVSSAC) hold their annual high\r\n\r\nschool boys basketball, girls basketball, volleyball, baseball, tennis and track and field state\r\n\r\ntournaments in the Charleston area throughout the year.\r\n\r\nBoys Basketball - March\r\n\r\nGirls Basketball - March\r\n\r\nVolleyball - November\r\n\r\nBaseball - June\r\n\r\nTennis - April\r\n\r\nTrack and Field - April\r\n\r\nSportsfest Meets WV Games\r\n\r\nSportsFEST includes the Jet Ski Hyrdo-Turf National Championship and the EVP Pro Am\r\n\r\nBeach Championship. WV Games, the largest collection of sanctioned sporting events in West\r\n\r\nVirginia, includes events such as a cornhole tournament, crossfit, tabata bootcamp, slalom\r\n\r\nskateboarding, wrestling, Jiu Jitsu and the West Virginia Storm will be stunting and tumbling. In\r\n\r\ntotal, more than 400 professional athletes will compete this weekend.\r\n\r\nCapital City Challenge\r\n\r\nSeptember 19, 2015\r\n\r\n4.2 mile Run, 4.2 mile Row, 16.8 mile Ride\r\n\r\nRun, Row &amp; Ride through the capital city on this flat, fast course that showcases the beauty of\r\n\r\ndowntown Charleston. This unique yet competitive event is designed for competitors of all\r\n\r\nfitness and skill levels. This family-friendly challenge features a post-race picnic with music, kids\'\r\n\r\nactivities, and great prizes. Solo and team entries are welcome.\r\n\r\n  \r\n\r\nBest Time of the Year\r\n\r\nThere\'s always opportunities to watch and participate in sports in the Charleston area! Outdoor\r\n\r\nevents are primarily available in late spring to early fall.',	'Sports Fan',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'194-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-06-30 08:30:35',	'2015-06-30 12:30:35',	'',	194,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/194-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
