</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3>Craik-Patton House</h3>\r\nCraik-Patton House was built about 1834 in the Greek Revival style. It is open for tours from April through October. It is listed on the National Register of Historic Places since 1970.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">2809 Kanawha Blvd. E.\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\n<a href=\"http://www.craik-patton.org/\" target=\"_blank\">craik-patton.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Coal Heritage Trail</h3>\r\nA driving trail that winds through over 187 rugged miles of scenic industrial heritage. You will pass through National Historic Districts and the physical remnants of the coal boom such as coal miners\' homes, company stores, company offices and more.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">100 Kelly Avenue\r\nOak Hill, WV 25901\r\n<a href=\"http://www.coalheritage.org\" target=\"_blank\">coalheritage.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Blenko Glass</h3>\r\nFor over 100 years, Blenko has maintained the tradition of hand making glassware in America. They offer a wide range of products which include functional glassware, art glass, mouth blown sheet glass, dalle de verre and other quality products. Tours are available.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">9 Bill Blenko Drive\r\nMilton, WV 25541\r\n<a href=\"http://www.blenko.com/\" target=\"_blank\">blenko.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Kanawha Blvd. Historical Markers</h3>\r\nAs you stroll along the riverbank, you will come across a series of historic markers commemorating moments in West Virginia history. These markers are part of the over 1,000 markers throughout the state marking sites of significance.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\r\n<h4>Best Events</h4>\r\n<h4><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-367\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/capitol_night_-shutter-1-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"capitol_night_-shutter (1)\" width=\"210\" height=\"140\" /></h4>\r\n<h3>Battle of Scary Creek/Skirmish at Hurricane Bridge - Civil War Reenactment</h3>\r\nPart of a Civil War weekend in Hurricane, the event commemorates two engagements of the Civil War separated by a space of two years. The Battle of Scary Creek., July 17, 1861 and the Blue and Gray Skirmish at Hurricane Bridge, March 28, 1863. Also, enjoy crafts, sutler\'s row, storytelling, a night firing, parade drills, a ladies tea, a historical lantern tour and a military dance.\r\n<h3>WV Day Celebrations</h3>\r\nCelebrate West Virginia\'s birthday with a variety of activities on the grounds of the WV State Capitol.\r\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\r\nHistory is happening every day of the year and this is certainly the case for those wanting to learn more about Charleston and West Virginia\'s history.\r\n\r\n</div>',	'History Buff',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'191-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-06-30 15:31:59',	'2015-06-30 19:31:59',	'',	191,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/191-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(374,	3,	'2015-06-30 15:39:55',	'2015-06-30 19:39:55',	'<h2>The music of the Charleston area is a diverse and eclectic mix, sure to please the ears of all looking for some great tunes. Live performances are abundant in the area at small and large venues as well as a variety of special events.</h2>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-1-cb\">\r\n<h3>Empty Glass</h3>\r\n\r\nLocated under a 3-story house jacked up in the air in Charlestons historically diverse East End. Here you will find delicious food, great  conversation, friendly spirits and live original music from all over the planet.\r\n\r\n410 Elizabeth St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\nwww.emptyglass.com\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Mountain Stage</h3>\r\n\r\nFor over 30 years \"Mountain Stage w/ Larry Groce\" has been the home of live music on public radio. Founded in 1983 in Charleston, WV and is produced by West Virginia Public Radio the show travels but most are recorded at the WV State Capitol Complex.\r\n\r\nCulture Center Theater\r\nCapitol Complex\r\n1900 Kanawha Boulevard East\r\nCharleston WV 25305\r\nwww.mountainstage.org\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nTaylor Books\r\n\r\nIn addition to an open mic night and scheduled performances, they have a broad selection of books, wide variety of hard-to-find magazines and unique collection of cards and gifts as well as an Art Annex.\r\n\r\n226 Capitol St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\nwww.taylorbooks.com\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWV Symphony Orchestra\r\n\r\nThe West Virginia Symphony Orchestra presents classical, pops, family &amp; chamber-music concerts annually. The WVSO also provides affordable, high-quality concerts, collaborations with arts organizations and a nationally award-winning education program.\r\n\r\nOne Clay Square \r\nCharleston, WV 25301 \r\nwvsymphony.org\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nLive on the Levee\r\n\r\nAn outdoor concert series presented by the City of Charleston, WV. The concerts take place each Friday from Memorial Day Weekend to Labor Day Weekend.\r\n\r\nKanawha Blvd.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\nliveontheleveecharleston.com\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n\r\nBrown Bag Concerts\r\n\r\nFree Lunchtime Concerts in Davis Park the third Wednesday of the month from May until September. The concerts last from 11:30am to 1:30pm. \r\n\r\nDavis Park\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nFret and Fiddle\r\n\r\nFret \'n Fiddle offers new and used string instruments. Specializing in vintage instruments, including guitars, mandolins, banjos and fiddles. They also offer consigned merchandise and a recording studio.\r\n\r\n809 Pennsylvania Ave.\r\nSt Albans, WV 25177\r\nwww.fretnfiddle.com\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSullivan\'s Records\r\n\r\nCharleston\'s newest record store! They specialize in vinyl, with thousands of new &amp; used records in stock, as well as tons of CD\'s, DVD\'s, and more.\r\n\r\n1588-A Washington St E,\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\nhttp://sullivansrecords.com/\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWV Music Hall of Fame\r\n\r\nThe WV Music Hall of Fame has a satellite exhibit in the Dickinson Street parking. The display features instruments, photos, posters and vintage memorabilia from Mountain Stage musicians  with an emphasis on those from the Kanawha Valley.\r\n\r\nQuarrier and Dickenson Sts.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\nhttp://www.wvmusichalloffame.com/\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n\r\n\r\nBest Events\r\n\r\nVandalia Gathering\r\n\r\nThe Vandalia Gathering brings together the finest traditional Appalachian musicians for a weekend of great picking. Elder statesmen and young upstarts perform on stage, compete in contests and play in impromptu jam sessions all over the Capitol Complex. Visitors to the Gathering can enjoy fiddle, banjo, mandolin and guitar contests outside during the day, and concerts in the State Theater in the evenings. Food and craft vendors are also part of the festival.\r\n\r\nSymphony Sunday\r\n\r\nFree day of music with the WV Symphony Orchestra and other musicians on the lawn of the University of Charleston. Artisan tents and food vendors are also present throughout the day. The day ends with the Symphony playing and fireworks.\r\n\r\nWine &amp; All That Jazz Festival\r\n\r\nPart of FestivAll, Charlestons Fund for the Arts produces this day long concert and lawn party. West Virginia wineries sell glasses and bottles of a variety of wines, jazz musicians take the stage and attendees enjoy the lawn of the University of Charleston.\r\n\r\n\r\nBest Time of the Year\r\n\r\nSummer is a music lover\'s paradise in the Charleston area. With a large variety of outdoor concerts and events, there\'s always an opportunity to enjoy the sweet sounds of summer in Charlie West.\r\n\r\n</div>',	'Music Lover',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'196-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-06-30 15:39:55',	'2015-06-30 19:39:55',	'',	196,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/196-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(375,	3,	'2015-08-17 15:33:11',	'2015-08-17 19:33:11',	'<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\n<h4>Best Events for Music Lovers</h4>\n[caption id=\"attachment_683\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"222\"]<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/2013-FestivALL-Charleston-WAATJ-drinkers-Saul.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-683\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/2013-FestivALL-Charleston-WAATJ-drinkers-Saul-300x199.jpg\" alt=\"Wine and All That Jazz.  Photo Credit:  FestivAll\" width=\"222\" height=\"147\" /></a> Wine and All That Jazz. Photo Credit: FestivAll[/caption]\n<h3>Vandalia Gathering</h3>\nThe Vandalia Gathering brings together the finest traditional Appalachian musicians for a weekend of great picking. Elder statesmen and young upstarts perform on stage, compete in contests and play in impromptu jam sessions all over the Capitol Complex. Visitors to the Gathering can enjoy fiddle, banjo, mandolin and guitar contests outside during the day, and concerts in the State Theater in the evenings. Food and craft vendors are also part of the festival.\n<h3>Symphony Sunday</h3>\nFree day of music with the WV Symphony Orchestra and other musicians on the lawn of the University of Charleston. Artisan tents and food vendors are also present throughout the day. The day ends with the Symphony playing and fireworks.\n<h3>Wine &amp; All That Jazz Festival</h3>\nPart of FestivAll, Charlestons Fund for the Arts produces this day long concert and lawn party. West Virginia wineries sell glasses and bottles of a variety of wines, jazz musicians take the stage and attendees enjoy the lawn of the University of Charleston.\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\nSummer is a music lover\'s paradise in the Charleston area. With a large variety of outdoor concerts and events, there\'s always an opportunity to enjoy the sweet sounds of summer in Charlie West.\n\n</div>\n<div class=\"content-block col-container-cb\">\n<h2>T