n\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">1555 Farnsworth Drive\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://friendsofspringhillcemetery.org/\" target=\"_blank\">friendsofspringhillcemetery.org</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3>Coal River Walhonde Water Trail</h3>\r\nThe Coal River offers a water trail great for kayaking, canoeing in addition to fishing. The river contains spotted and smallmouth bass, channel catfish, striper, walleye and muskie.\r\n\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\"><a href=\"http://coalrivergroup.com/\" target=\"_blank\">coalrivergroup.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Cabela\'s</h3>\r\nLocated in the Southridge Shopping Centre, Cabelas offers 80,000 sq feet of outdoor merchandise including sporting and camping goods. The building is a log cabin and stonework style building with a large waterfall display inside.\r\n\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">200 Cross Terrace Blvd\r\nCharleston, WV 25309\r\n<a href=\"http://www.cabelas.com\" target=\"_blank\">cabelas.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Hatfield and McCoy Trails</h3>\r\nEight trail systems stretch over 700 total miles of WV allowing UTV, ATV, dirt bike riders with a world-class trail system. All trails are open 365 days a year and new trails are being added.\r\n\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">28 Big Pinnacle Branch Rd.\r\nJulian, WV 25529\r\n<a href=\"http://www.trailsheaven.com\" target=\"_blank\">trailsheaven.com</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\r\n<h3>Best Events</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-282 alignleft\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/sunrise1-220x300.jpg\" alt=\"sunrise1\" width=\"190\" height=\"260\" />\r\n<h3>Margaret Denison Fall Nature Walks</h3>\r\nAt Kanawha State Forest, guided wildflower walks on various trails throughout the forest. Specific hikes include: fall wildflowers, fungi,birds, trees and natural history. Don\'t miss this opportunity to learn about the life of the Forest.\r\n<h3>Festivall Sunrise Trail</h3>\r\nTake a shaded stroll on the charming Sunrise Carriage Trail and enjoy music, dance and art along the way.\r\n<h3>East End Garden Showcase</h3>\r\nThis urban gardening showcase takes you on a stroll through the Historic East End of  Charleston.  Visit residential gardens that each serve as a tiny oasis from the hustle and bustle of the busy East End district.\r\n<h3>Tour de Coal</h3>\r\nThe Tour de Coal, a \"paddling event\" for canoes and kayaks normally held in June, is an 11-mile trip from Upper Falls to St. Albans. Paddlers negotiate the Lower Falls, a one-mile rapid along the route.\r\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\r\nSpring and fall serve as the best times in the Kanawha Valley for exploring nature.  The weather is pleasant and not too hot allowing for longer times outside surrounded by mother nature.\r\n</div>',	'Nature Lover',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'204-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-06-30 16:08:41',	'2015-06-30 20:08:41',	'',	204,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/204-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(386,	3,	'2015-06-30 16:21:06',	'2015-06-30 20:21:06',	'<h2>Whether you want fast-paced excitement, great music or a low-key culinary experience, theres always something to do late-night in Charleston!</h2>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-1-cb\">\r\n<h3>Comedy Zone</h3>\r\nTwo of the nation\'s funniest comedians travel to Charleston to entertain the crowds. Full food and drink menus available during the show. Shows are Fridays at 8pm &amp; Saturdays at 7pm and 9pm.\r\n\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">400 2nd Ave.\r\nCharleston, WV 25303\r\n<a href=\"http://comedyzonecharleston.com\" target=\"_blank\">comedyzonecharleston.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Capitol Street Nightlife</h3>\r\nCapitol Street &amp; adjacent Kanawha Blvd. have a variety of bars/lounges for all scenes. Whether youre looking for a great glass of wine, sports bar, irish pub or game of pool, its all here!\r\n\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Capitol St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Bricks and Barrels</h3>\r\nIf you\'re looking for an upscale evening, Bricks and Barrels is the place. Sit in one of the Barrel shaped booths and enjoy their large variety of beers and wines along with their eclectic menu.\r\n\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">1214 Smith St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.bricksnbarrels.com/\" target=\"_blank\">bricksnbarrels.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Empty Glass</h3>\r\nLocated under a 3-story house jacked up in the air in Charlestons historically diverse East End. Here you will find delicious food, great conversation, friendly spirits and live original music.\r\n\r\n410 Elizabeth St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\"><a href=\"http://www.emptyglass.com\" target=\"_blank\">emptyglass.com</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3>Celsius</h3>\r\nAn upscale lounge serving wine, craft beers and specialty cocktails. The food menu includes burgers, salads, flat breads and a unique variety of dishes.\r\n\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">212 Hale St\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/CelsiusWV\" target=\"_blank\">facebook.com/CelsiusWV</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Timothy\'s</h3>\r\nTimothys is located directly below the Quarrier Diner. Watch your favorite sports on any one of the 17 high definition flat screens. They are constantly hosting events from live music, trivia nights and more.\r\n\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">1022 Quarrier St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.timothyssportsbar.com/\" target=\"_blank\">timothyssportsbar.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Mardi Gras Casino</h3>\r\nOver 90,000 square feet of gaming space, the Mardi Gras Casino offers over 30 table games, over 1,000 slot machines, greyhound racing, restaurants and bars and much more!\r\n\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">#1 Greyhound Drive\r\nCross Lanes, WV 25313\r\n<a href=\"http://www.mardigrascasinowv.com/\" target=\"_blank\">mardigrascasinowv.com</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\r\n<h4>Best Events</h4>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-294 aligncenter\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/live_on_levee1-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"live_on_levee1\" width=\"210\" height=\"210\" />\r\n<h3>Live On The Levee</h3>\r\nOutdoor concert series presented by the City of Charleston, WV. The concerts take place each Friday from Memorial Day Weekend to Labor Day Weekend.\r\n<h3>East End Pub Crawl</h3>\r\nJoin in on the St. Patrick\'s Day fun on the East End of Charleston.  Live, local Celtic music from FOOTMAD, walk from bar to bar (over 10) enjoying drink specials and look for the hidden shamrocks throughout the area in order to win big!\r\n<h3>Boo Bash</h3>\r\nAll the ghosts and goblins come out to play at this traditional-style Halloween party.  Dance the night away with the event\'s DJ and enjoy great food and drinks, games and a photo booth. Hosted by the South Charleston Chamber of Commerce, its a fun-filled fright night!\r\n<h3>HallowEast</h3>\r\nIf you\'re looking for a spooky time, HallowEast has lots of events to make your Halloween. ArtMares, Main Street Murder Mystery, East End Zombie Walk, Run Like Hell Zombie 5K and the Costume Crawl are all exciting events that make this week of scary a truly ghouly experience.\r\n<h3>Murder Mysteries</h3>\r\nThese exciting Who-Dun-It events are sure to entertain the best of detectives.  Located at the Comedy Zone in the Holiday Inn &amp; Suites, participants enjoy a buffet dinner and an entertaining interactive show with a different theme each time.\r\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\r\nThere\'s always time to party!  But if you\'re looking for great times with special events, look around the holidays...particularly St. Patty\'s Day and  Halloween!<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/murder.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-293\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/murder-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"murder\" width=\"210\" height=\"158\" /></a>\r\n\r\n</div>',	'Night Owl',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'200-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-06-30 16:21:06',	'2015-06-30 20:21:06',	'',	200,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/200-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
