ams consist of baseball, basketball, football, golf, tennis, softball, cross country and volleyball.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">500 Fairlawn Ave.\r\nInstitute, WV 25112\r\n<a href=\"http://www.wvsuyellowjackets.com\" target=\"_blank\">wvsuyellowjackets.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3>Charleston Civic Center</h3>\r\nHosts a variety of annual sporting events including WVSSAC Boys and Girls Basketball State Tournaments, archery and volleyball tournaments, Mountain East Conference Championships, boxing/martial arts events, Capital Classic between WVU and Marshall Men\'s Basketball.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">200 Civic Center Dr.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.charlestonwvciviccenter.com\" target=\"_blank\">charlestonwvciviccenter.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Trace Fork Soccer Complex</h3>\r\nThe Friends of Coal Fields At Trace Fork Soccer Complex is a six field soccer complex is located at the Shops at Trace Fork, just off U.S. Rt. 119 south of Charleston, West Virginia.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">25 RHL Blvd.\r\nSouth Charleston, WV 25309\r\n<a href=\"http://traceforksoccer.com/\" target=\"_blank\">traceforksoccer.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Adelphia Sports Bar and Grille</h3>\r\nVoted best appetizer and wings in the valley three years in a row! Adelphia infuses Greek and American cuisine to offer some of the best food around. Open 365 days a year and full menu served until midnight and later.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">218 Capitol Street\r\nCharleston WV, 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://adelphiasportsbar.com/\" target=\"_blank\">http://adelphiasportsbar.com/</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>South Charleston Memorial Ice Arena</h3>\r\nNewly opened, state-of-the-art facility with amenities like an arcade and heated seating area that will accommodate 500 spectators. Groups of all sizes are welcome.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">20 RHL Blvd.\r\nCharleston, WV 25309\r\n<a href=\"http://cityofsouthcharleston.com/memorial-ice-arena/\" target=\"_blank\">memorial-ice-arena/</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Little Creek Park</h3>\r\nThe park has five baseball/softball fields, seven soccer fields, a football field, two tennis courts and two basketball courts. Also, 18-hold disc golf course and soap box derby track are located at the park.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">1 Little Creek Park Rd.\r\nSouth Charleston, WV 25309\r\n<a href=\"http://cityofsouthcharleston.com/little-creek-park/\" target=\"_blank\">little-creek-park/</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n<div><iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/embed?mid=zF2Ov4mSNUbs.kjg5elzGTzXs\" width=\"460\" height=\"325\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>',	'Sports Fan',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'194-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-07-02 08:39:47',	'2015-07-02 12:39:47',	'',	194,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/194-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(488,	3,	'2015-07-02 08:55:26',	'2015-07-02 12:55:26',	'<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\r\n<h3>Best Events</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-282 alignleft\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/sunrise1-220x300.jpg\" alt=\"sunrise1\" width=\"190\" height=\"260\" />\r\n<h3>Margaret Denison Fall Nature Walks</h3>\r\nAt Kanawha State Forest, guided wildflower walks on various trails throughout the forest. Specific hikes include: fall wildflowers, fungi,birds, trees and natural history. Don\'t miss this opportunity to learn about the life of the Forest.\r\n<h3>Festivall Sunrise Trail</h3>\r\nTake a shaded stroll on the charming Sunrise Carriage Trail and enjoy music, dance and art along the way.\r\n<h3>East End Garden Showcase</h3>\r\nThis urban gardening showcase takes you on a stroll through the Historic East End of  Charleston.  Visit residential gardens that each serve as a tiny oasis from the hustle and bustle of the busy East End district.\r\n<h3>Tour de Coal</h3>\r\nThe Tour de Coal, a \"paddling event\" for canoes and kayaks normally held in June, is an 11-mile trip from Upper Falls to St. Albans. Paddlers negotiate the Lower Falls, a one-mile rapid along the route.\r\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\r\nSpring and fall serve as the best times in the Kanawha Valley for exploring nature.  The weather is pleasant and not too hot allowing for longer times outside surrounded by mother nature.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-container-cb\">\r\n<h2>Nestled in the heart of the Appalachian mountains, Charleston offers opportunities for any type of nature lover. Whether long hikes or wildlife  viewing, youre sure to gain a new love for the outdoors in the Kanawha Valley.</h2>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-1-cb\">\r\n<h3>Kanawha State Forest</h3>\r\n9,300-acres of picnicking, hiking, mountain biking and cross-country skiing, bird-watching, the forest is known for having some of the best hiking trails in the area and for also hosting events throughout the year.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">7500 Kanawha State Forest Drive\r\nCharleston, WV 25314\r\n<a href=\"http://www.kanawhastateforest.com/\" target=\"_blank\">kanawhastateforest.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>The Sunrise Carriage Trail</h3>\r\nThe Sunrise Carriage Trail is a peaceful and varied landscape of towering trees, wildflowers, ornamental plantings, and historic masonry remains. The trail is 0.65 miles with incredible views of the city.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">746 Myrtle Road\r\nCharleston, WV 25314\r\n<a href=\"http://www.carriagetrail.org/\" target=\"_blank\">carriagetrail.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Little Creek Park</h3>\r\nRock formations, such as Devil\'s Tea Table are quite popular for hikers to discover. Little Creek also has picnic shelters, playgrounds, baseball/softball fields, soccer fields, football field, tennis courts, basketball courts, and an 18-hold disc golf course.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">1 Little Creek Park Rd.\r\nSouth Charleston, WV 25309\r\n<a href=\"http://cityofsouthcharleston.com/little-creek-park/\" target=\"_blank\">cityofsouthcharleston.com/little-creek-park</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Bird Watching at Spring Hill Cemetery</h3>\r\nAmongst the historical gravesites of city founders, are trees that provide sanctuary for a variety of bird species at the cemetery. Bird walks are held on Sunday mornings during peak migration seasons.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">1555 Farnsworth Drive\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://friendsofspringhillcemetery.org/\" target=\"_blank\">friendsofspringhillcemetery.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3>Coal River Walhonde Water Trail</h3>\r\nThe Coal River offers a water trail great for kayaking, canoeing in addition to fishing. The river contains spotted and smallmouth bass, channel catfish, striper, walleye and muskie.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\"><a href=\"http://coalrivergroup.com/\" target=\"_blank\">coalrivergroup.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Cabela\'s</h3>\r\nLocated in the Southridge Shopping Centre, Cabelas offers 80,000 sq feet of outdoor merchandise including sporting and camping goods. The building is a log cabin and stonework style building with a large waterfall display inside.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">200 Cross Terrace Blvd\r\nCharleston, WV 25309\r\n<a href=\"http://www.cabelas.com\" target=\"_blank\">cabelas.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Hatfield and McCoy Trails</h3>\r\nEight trail systems stretch over 700 total miles of WV allowing UTV, ATV, dirt bike riders with a world-class trail system. All trails are open 365 days a year and new trails are being added.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">28 Big Pinnacle Branch Rd.\r\nJulian, WV 25529\r\n<a href=\"http://www.trailsheaven.com\" target=\"_blank\">trailsheaven.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n<div><iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/embed?mid=zF2Ov4mSNUbs.k6T2yNzKwbB8\" width=\"460\" height=\"325\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>',	'Nature Lover',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'204-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-07-02 08:55:26',	'2015-07-02 12:55:26',	'',	204,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/204-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(489,	3,	'2015-07-02 09:02:41',	'2015-07-02 13:02:41',	'<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\r\n<h4>Best Events</h4>\r\n<h3>Vandalia Gathering</h3>\r\nThe Vandalia Gathering brings together the finest traditional Appalachian musicians for a weekend of great picking. Elder statesmen and young upstarts perform on stage, compete in contests and play in impromptu jam sessions all over the Capitol Complex. Visitors to the Gathering can enjoy fiddle, banjo, mandolin and guitar contests outside during the day, and concerts in the State Theater in the evenings. Food and craft vendors are also part of the festival.\r\n<h3>Symphony Sunday</h3>\r\nFree day of music with the WV Symphony Orchestra and other musicians on the lawn of the University of Charleston. Artisan tents and food vendors are also present throughout the day. The day ends with the Symphony playing and fireworks.\r\n<h3>Wine &amp; All That Jazz Festival</h3>\r\nPart of FestivAll, Charlestons Fund for the Arts produces this day long concert and lawn party. West Virginia wineries sell glasses and bottles of a variety of wines, jazz musicians take the stage and attendees enjoy the lawn of the University of Charleston.\r\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\r\nSummer is a music lover\'s paradise in the Charleston area. With a large variety of outdoor concerts and events, there\'s always an opportunity to enjoy the sweet sounds of summer in Charlie West.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-container-cb\">\r\n<h2>The music of the Charleston area is a diverse and eclectic mix, sure to please the ears of all looking for some great tunes. Live performances are abundant in the area at small and large venues as well as a variety of special events.</h2>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-1-cb\">\r\n<h3>Empty Glass</h3>\r\nLocated under a 3-story house jacked up in the air in Charlestons historically diverse East End. Here you will find delicious food, great conversation, friendly spirits and live original music from all over the planet.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">410 Elizabeth St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\n<a href=\"http://www.emptyglass.com\" target=\"_blank\">emptyglass.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Mountain Stage</h3>\r\nFor over 30 years \"Mountain Stage w/ Larry Groce\" has been the home of live music on public radio. Founded in 1983 in Charleston, WV and is produced by West Virginia Public Radio the show travels but most are recorded at the WV State Capitol Complex.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Culture Center Theater\r\nCapitol Complex\r\n1900 Kanawha Boulevard East\r\nCharleston WV 25305\r\n<a href=\"http://www.mountainstage.org\" target=\"_blank\">mountainstage.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Taylor Books</h3>\r\nIn addition to an open mic night and scheduled performances, they have a broad selection of books, wide variety of hard-to-find magazines and unique collection of cards and gifts as well as an Art Annex.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">226 Capitol St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.taylorbooks.com\" target=\"_blank\">taylorbooks.com</a></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>WV Symphony Orchestra</h3>\r\nThe West Virginia Symphony Orchestra presents classical, pops, family &amp; chamber-music concerts annually. The WVSO also provides affordable, high-quality concerts, collaborations with arts organizations and a nationally award-winning education program.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">One Clay Square\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://wvsymphony.org\" target=\"_blank\">wvsymphony.org</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n\r\n<h3>Live on the Levee</h3>\r\nAn outdoor concert series presented by the City of Charleston, WV. The concerts take place each Friday from Memorial Day Weekend to Labor Day Weekend.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Kanawha Blvd.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://liveontheleveecharleston.com\" target=\"_blank\">liveontheleveecharleston.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Brown Bag Concerts</h3>\r\nFree Lunchtime Concerts in Davis Park the third Wednesday of the month from May until September. The concerts last from 11:30am to 1:30pm.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Davis Park\r\nCharleston, WV 25301</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Fret and Fiddle</h3>\r\nFret \'n Fiddle offers new and used string instruments. Specializing in vintage instruments, including guitars, mandolins, banjos and fiddles. They also offer consigned merchandise and a recording studio.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">809 Pennsylvania Ave.\r\nSt Albans, WV 25177\r\n<a href=\"http://www.fretnfiddle.com\" target=\"_blank\">fretnfiddle.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Sullivan\'s Records</h3>\r\nCharleston\'s newest record store! They specialize in vinyl, with thousands of new &amp; used records in stock, as well as tons of CD\'s, DVD\'s, and more.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">1588-A Washington St E,\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\n<a href=\"http://sullivansrecords.com/\" target=\"_blank\">sullivansrecords.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>WV Music Hall of Fame</h3>\r\nThe WV Music Hall of Fame has a satellite exhibit in the Dickinson Street parking. The display features instruments, photos, posters and vintage memorabilia from Mountain Stage musicians  with an emphasis on those from the Kanawha Valley.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Quarrier and Dickenson Sts.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.wvmusichalloffame.com/\" target=\"_blank\">www.wvmusichalloffame.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n<div><iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/embed?mid=zF2Ov4mSNUbs.kOJvQgaood6w\" width=\"460\" height=\"325\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>',	'Music Lover',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'196-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-07-02 09:02:41',	'2015-07-02 13:02:41',	'',	196,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/196-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(490,	3,	'2015-07-02 09:11:55',	'2015-07-02 13:11:55',	'<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\r\n<h4>Best Events</h4>\r\n<h4><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-367\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/capitol_night_-shutter-1-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"capitol_night_-shutter (1)\" width=\"210\" height=\"140\" /></h4>\r\n<h3>Battle of Scary Creek/Skirmish at Hurricane Bridge - Civil War Reenactment</h3>\r\nPart of a Civil War weekend in Hurricane, the event commemorates two engagements of the Civil War separated by a space of two years. The Battle of Scary Creek., July 17, 1861 and the Blue and Gray Skirmish at Hurricane Bridge, March 28, 1863. Also, enjoy crafts, sutler\'s row, storytelling, a night firing, parade drills, a ladies tea, a historical lantern tour and a military dance.\r\n<h3>WV Day Celebrations</h3>\r\nCelebrate West Virginia\'s birthday with a variety of activities on the grounds of the WV State Capitol.\r\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\r\nHistory is happening every day of the year and this is certainly the case for those wanting to learn more about Charleston and West Virginia\'s history.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-container-cb\">\r\n<h2>Charlestons diverse opportunities for entertainment, fun and learning makes it a great place to visit and to live! Heres a few ideas for the city explorer in all of us.</h2>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-1-cb\">\r\n<h3>WV State Museum</h3>\r\nThis free-to-the-public museum offers an interactive look into the history, culture and treasures of West Virginia. The museum is designed as a timeline telling story of WV. A museum gift shop offers WV locally-made products.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">WV Division of Culture and History\r\nCapitol Complex\r\n1900 Kanawha Boulevard East\r\nCharleston WV 25305\r\n<a href=\"http://www.wvculture.org/museum/State-Museum-Index.html\" target=\"_blank\">WV-State-Museum</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>WV Humanities Council</h3>\r\nThe Council provides constant events and programs promoting the Mountain State and it\'s art, literature and history. It is located at the MacFarland-Hubbard House, which is listed on the National Register of Historic Places.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">1310 Kanawha Blvd., E.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.wvhumanities.org/\" target=\"_blank\">wvhumanities.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Malden</h3>\r\nHistoric town just east of Charleston. VIsit Booker T. Washington\'s childhood home, African Zion Baptist Church, J.Q. Dickenson Salt and many other historic buildings and sites.\r\n<h3>Governors Mansion</h3>\r\nTours of the Governor\'s Mansion begin on the front porch of the Mansion on Thursdays and Fridays. Reservations are required and are honored on a first-come, first-serve basis. Call for reservations at 304-558-4839.\r\n<h3>West Virginia State Capitol</h3>\r\nTours begin on the first floor Rotunda. Groups under 10 are welcome to join a regularly scheduled tour without reservations. Groups of more than 10 are best served with a reservation and tours of Senate/Representatives chamber require reservations. 304-558-2601\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3>Craik-Patton House</h3>\r\nCraik-Patton House was built about 1834 in the Greek Revival style. It is open for tours from April through October. It is listed on the National Register of Historic Places since 1970.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">2809 Kanawha Blvd. E.\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\n<a href=\"http://www.craik-patton.org/\" target=\"_blank\">craik-patton.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Coal Heritage Trail</h3>\r\nA driving trail that winds through over 187 rugged miles of scenic industrial heritage. You will pass through National Historic Districts and the physical remnants of the coal boom such as coal miners\' homes, company stores, company offices and more.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">100 Kelly Avenue\r\nOak Hill, WV 25901\r\n<a href=\"http://www.coalheritage.org\" target=\"_blank\">coalheritage.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Blenko Glass</h3>\r\nFor over 100 years, Blenko has maintained the tradition of hand making glassware in America. They offer a wide range of products which include functional glassware, art glass, mouth blown sheet glass, dalle de verre and other quality products. Tours are available.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">9 Bill Blenko Drive\r\nMilton, WV 25541\r\n<a href=\"http://www.blenko.com/\" target=\"_blank\">blenko.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Kanawha Blvd. Historical Markers</h3>\r\nAs you stroll along the riverbank, you will come across a series of historic markers commemorating moments in West Virginia history. These markers are part of the over 1,000 markers throughout the state marking sites of significance.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n<div><iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/embed?mid=zF2Ov4mSNUbs.kIo4W4VDDTqM\" width=\"460\" height=\"325\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>',	'History Buff',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'191-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-07-02 09:11:55',	'2015-07-02 13:11:55',	'',	191,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/191-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(491,	3,	'2015-07-02 09:17:59',	'2015-07-02 13:17:59',	'<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\r\n<h4>Best Events for Families</h4>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/FestivALL_2014_Childrens_Art_Fair_11_SMALLER_Sava_-__Javins_authorized.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-253\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/FestivALL_2014_Childrens_Art_Fair_11_SMALLER_Sava_-__Javins_authorized-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"FestivALL_2014_Childrens_Art_Fair_11_SMALLER_Sava_-__Javins_authorized\" width=\"210\" height=\"140\" /></a>\r\n<h3>Clay Center Family Fun Days</h3>\r\nEach day is full of family entertainment with themed science and art activities taking place throughout the day in addition to our three floors of art and science exhibits.\r\n<h3>Children\'s Art Fair and Kanawha County Public Library Street Fair</h3>\r\nA perfect combination for two days of family fun: Make &amp; take craft opportunities from invited artisans and groups, a sale of work by children and youth in Kanawha County neighborhood programs; a stage with child-friendly performances\r\n<h3>Movie Nights at Magic Island</h3>\r\nSponsored by local radio station, WQBE, Magic Island becomes a free, family friendly movie theater under the stars. The Island opens up at 6 with a Kids Zone &amp; the movie will start around dusk! Movie Nights take place Wednesday nights in June.\r\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\r\nAll year long there\'s plenty of Family Fun in Charleston, WV!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-container-cb\">\r\n<h2>Charleston is a great place for families!  With so many exciting kid-friendly activities including sports, arts and food, theres never a dull moment. For more ideas for family fun, check out our event calendar.</h2>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-1-cb\">\r\n<h3>WV Power</h3>\r\nMinor League baseball team in the South Atlantic League. The Class A Pittsburgh Pirates affiliate plays home games at Appalachian Power Park, also home to the WVSSAC baseball tournament.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Appalachian Power Park\r\n601 Morris St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://wvpower.com\" target=\"_blank\">wvpower.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Public Libraries</h3>\r\nOur local libraries are great places for fun and learning! Many events, programs &amp; services are free to the public. Kanawha County public library also provides geocaching equipment for rent.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Kanawha County Public Library\r\n123 Capitol St\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://kanawhalibrary.org/\" target=\"_blank\">kanawhalibrary.org</a></p>\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">South Charleston Public Library\r\n312 4th Avenue\r\nSouth Charleston WV 25303\r\n<a href=\"http://www.southcharlestonlibrary.org/\" target=\"_blank\">southcharlestonlibrary.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Chuck E Cheese</h3>\r\nLocated at Southridge Centre, Chuck E. Cheeses is a kid-centric experience. Admission is free and games require tokens that can be purchased. There\'s also a show consisting of characters &amp; music.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">2846 Mountaineer Blvd.\r\nCharleston, WV, 25309\r\n<a href=\"http://www.chuckecheese.com/\" target=\"_blank\">chuckecheese.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Waterways</h3>\r\nWaterways offers pool, tube &amp; body slides, lazy river, walking trail, unlimited putt-putt golf and kiddie island. Shelters available for family outings. Concession food is available for meals and snacks.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">109 Water Way\r\nAlkol, WV 25501\r\n<a href=\"http://waterwayspark.net/\" target=\"_blank\">waterwayspark.net</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3>Clay Center for the Arts and Sciences</h3>\r\nA 240,000 sq ft structure housing performing &amp; visual arts and sciences under one roof. Home to the Avampato Discovery Museum, Juliet Museum of Art and Maier Foundation Performance\r\nHall.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">One Clay Square\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.theclaycenter.org/\" target=\"_blank\">theclaycenter.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>The Peanut Shoppe</h3>\r\nThe Peanut Shoppe has been a Charleston tradition for over 60 years. Established in 1950 by Delbert Moore, it is still in its original location. We recommend the chocolate stars!\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">126 Capitol St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/thepeanutshoppe\" target=\"_blank\">facebook.com/thepeanutshoppe</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Camden Park</h3>\r\nLooking for old-fashioned fun? Camden Park, WVs only amusement park, is a 26 acre park located near Huntington. Established in 1903, the park is home to more than thirty rides and\r\nattractions, including a full-size traditional wooden roller coaster and several other vintage rides.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">5000 Waverly Rd.\r\nHuntington, WV 25704\r\n<a href=\"http://www.camdenpark.com/\" target=\"_blank\">camdenpark.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Coonskin Park</h3>\r\nThe park includes over 1,000 acres of hiking/biking trails, an accessible 18 hole golf course, Olympic size pool, picnic shelters, tennis courts, horseshoe pits, playground, ampitheater,\r\nsoccer stadium and wedding garden.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">2000 Coonskin Drive\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\n<a href=\"http://www.kcprc.com/Parks/Coonskin-Park.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">Coonskin-Park</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n<div><iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/embed?mid=zF2Ov4mSNUbs.km_PDXqCqQi8\" width=\"460\" height=\"325\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>',	'Family Fun',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'202-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-07-02 09:17:59',	'2015-07-02 13:17:59',	'',	202,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/202-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
