(546,	3,	'2015-07-02 13:27:11',	'2015-07-02 17:27:11',	'<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\r\n<h4>Best Events for Families</h4>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_253\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"210\"]<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/FestivALL_2014_Childrens_Art_Fair_11_SMALLER_Sava_-__Javins_authorized.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-253\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/FestivALL_2014_Childrens_Art_Fair_11_SMALLER_Sava_-__Javins_authorized-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"FestivALL_2014_Childrens_Art_Fair_11_SMALLER_Sava_-__Javins_authorized\" width=\"210\" height=\"140\" /></a> Photo Courtesy of [/caption]\r\n<h3>Clay Center Family Fun Days</h3>\r\nEach day is full of family entertainment with themed science and art activities taking place throughout the day in addition to our three floors of art and science exhibits.\r\n<h3>Children\'s Art Fair and Kanawha County Public Library Street Fair</h3>\r\nA perfect combination for two days of family fun: Make &amp; take craft opportunities from invited artisans and groups, a sale of work by children and youth in Kanawha County neighborhood programs; a stage with child-friendly performances\r\n<h3>Movie Nights at Magic Island</h3>\r\nSponsored by local radio station, WQBE, Magic Island becomes a free, family friendly movie theater under the stars. The Island opens up at 6 with a Kids Zone &amp; the movie will start around dusk! Movie Nights take place Wednesday nights in June.\r\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\r\nAll year long there\'s plenty of Family Fun in Charleston, WV!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-container-cb\">\r\n<h2>Charleston is a great place for families!  With so many exciting kid-friendly activities including sports, arts and food, theres never a dull moment. For more ideas for family fun, check out our event calendar.</h2>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-1-cb\">\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/A-Map-Marker.png\" alt=\"A-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />WV Power</h3>\r\nMinor League baseball team in the South Atlantic League. The Class A Pittsburgh Pirates affiliate plays home games at Appalachian Power Park, also home to the WVSSAC baseball tournament.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Appalachian Power Park\r\n601 Morris St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://wvpower.com\" target=\"_blank\">wvpower.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-C-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Public Libraries</h3>\r\nOur local libraries are great places for fun and learning! Many events, programs &amp; services are free to the public. Kanawha County public library also provides geocaching equipment for rent.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Kanawha County Public Library\r\n123 Capitol St\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://kanawhalibrary.org/\" target=\"_blank\">kanawhalibrary.org</a></p>\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">South Charleston Public Library\r\n312 4th Avenue\r\nSouth Charleston WV 25303\r\n<a href=\"http://www.southcharlestonlibrary.org/\" target=\"_blank\">southcharlestonlibrary.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-C-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Chuck E Cheese</h3>\r\nLocated at Southridge Centre, Chuck E. Cheeses is a kid-centric experience. Admission is free and games require tokens that can be purchased. There\'s also a show consisting of characters &amp; music.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">2846 Mountaineer Blvd.\r\nCharleston, WV, 25309\r\n<a href=\"http://www.chuckecheese.com/\" target=\"_blank\">chuckecheese.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-C-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Waterways</h3>\r\nWaterways offers pool, tube &amp; body slides, lazy river, walking trail, unlimited putt-putt golf and kiddie island. Shelters available for family outings. Concession food is available for meals and snacks.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">109 Water Way\r\nAlkol, WV 25501\r\n<a href=\"http://waterwayspark.net/\" target=\"_blank\">waterwayspark.net</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-C-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Clay Center for the Arts and Sciences</h3>\r\nA 240,000 sq ft structure housing performing &amp; visual arts and sciences under one roof. Home to the Avampato Discovery Museum, Juliet Museum of Art and Maier Foundation Performance\r\nHall.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">One Clay Square\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.theclaycenter.org/\" target=\"_blank\">theclaycenter.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-C-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />The Peanut Shoppe</h3>\r\nThe Peanut Shoppe has been a Charleston tradition for over 60 years. Established in 1950 by Delbert Moore, it is still in its original location. We recommend the chocolate stars!\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">126 Capitol St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/thepeanutshoppe\" target=\"_blank\">facebook.com/thepeanutshoppe</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-C-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Camden Park</h3>\r\nLooking for old-fashioned fun? Camden Park, WVs only amusement park, is a 26 acre park located near Huntington. Established in 1903, the park is home to more than thirty rides and attractions, including a full-size traditional wooden roller coaster and several other vintage rides.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">5000 Waverly Rd.\r\nHuntington, WV 25704\r\n<a href=\"http://www.camdenpark.com/\" target=\"_blank\">camdenpark.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-C-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Coonskin Park</h3>\r\nThe park includes over 1,000 acres of hiking/biking trails, an accessible 18 hole golf course, Olympic size pool, picnic shelters, tennis courts, horseshoe pits, playground, ampitheater,\r\nsoccer stadium and wedding garden.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">2000 Coonskin Drive\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\n<a href=\"http://www.kcprc.com/Parks/Coonskin-Park.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">Coonskin-Park</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n<div><iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/embed?mid=zF2Ov4mSNUbs.km_PDXqCqQi8\" width=\"460\" height=\"325\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>',	'Family Fun',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'202-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-07-02 13:27:11',	'2015-07-02 17:27:11',	'',	202,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/202-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(547,	3,	'2015-07-02 13:28:53',	'2015-07-02 17:28:53',	'<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\r\n<h4>Best Events for Adrenaline Junkies</h4>\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-240\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/volleyball4-300x177.jpg\" alt=\"volleyball4\" width=\"210\" height=\"124\" />\r\n<h3>WV Games/Sportsfest</h3>\r\nCome out and enjoy jet ski racing, professional volleyball and tons more during this fun-filled weekend. The \"Governors\' Cup\" is the final stop of the Hydro-Turf Pro Watercross Tour, where\r\nthe pro riders who have been traveling the tour will be crowned the U.S.A. National Champions. Amateur, Novice and Junior competitors will also be vying for the National Amateur Championship title. For more information on the National Championship Pro Watercross Tour.\r\n<h3>Bridge Day</h3>\r\nBridge Day, one of the largest extreme sports event in the world, is held annually on the third Saturday in October in Fayette County, West Virginia (WV). Hundreds of BASE jumpers and nearly 80,000 spectators are expected to attend the event. Vendor booths and food are available on the bridge, along with the best overlook of the New River Gorge.\r\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\r\nFall is a great time to catch some great (and unique) events for adrenaline junkies.  September and October offer good weather but not hot conditions.\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-container-cb\">\r\n<h2>Climb zip, row and ride through the Charleston West Virginia area with these great heart-pumping activities.</h2>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-1-cb\">\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/A-Map-Marker.png\" alt=\"A-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Adventures on the Gorge</h3>\r\nAOTG offers a variety of adrenaline pumping adventures including whitewater rafting on the New and Gauley Rivers, canopy tours, zip lines, guided hiking, paintball, caving, horseback riding and more! With restaurants and kids camps, the whole family can really make a day of it!\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">219 Chestnutburg Rd.\r\nLansing, WV 25862\r\n<a href=\"http://www.adventuresonthegorge.com\" target=\"_blank\">adventuresonthegorge.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-C-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Hatfield and McCoy Trails</h3>\r\nEight trail systems stretch over 700 total miles of West Virginia allowing UTV, ATV, dirt bike riders with a world-class trail system. All trails are open 365 days a year and new trails are constantly being added.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">28 Big Pinnacle Branch Rd.\r\nJulian, WV 25529\r\n<a href=\"http://www.trailsheaven.com\" target=\"_blank\">trailsheaven.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-C-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />eNeRGy Rock Climbing Gym</h3>\r\nIndoor Rock Climbing Gym providing opportunities for beginners through experts to climb in the Charleston area. The gym features 16 ft tall 5, 10 and 15 degree overhanging walls, 14 ft tall 30\r\ndegree overhanging wall, a cave with 45, 60 and horizontal roof features/. The cave also has a 14 ft long hand crack that splits and an overhanging arete. In the loft area, there is a 13 ft tall 50 degree wall that is perfect for training. There is also a 13 ft tall \'wave\' wall for transitional angle training and a mushroom wall to practice mantling and topping out. Shoes available for rental and day passes (5-9pm) available for $12. No additional equipment needed prior to entry.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">269 Graham Dr.\r\nCharleston, WV 25302\r\n<a href=\"http://www.energyrockgym.com/\" target=\"_blank\">energyrockgym.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-C-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Hidden Trails Motorsports</h3>\r\nHidden Trails Motorsports sell new and used motorsports vehicles with brands including Can-Am, Sea-Doo, Spyder, Suzuki and all Yamaha brands. They also service and have parts available for the brands listed as well as powersports brands including Polaris, Kawasaki, Arctic Cat and Honda.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">3014 E Dupont Ave.\r\nBelle, WV 25015\r\n<a href=\"http://www.hiddentrailsmoto.com/\" target=\"_blank\">hiddentrailsmoto.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-C-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />BridgeWalk</h3>\r\nTake a walk along the bottom of the New River Gorge Bridge! This 2-3 hour tour will take guests from the Canyon Rim Visitor Center across the 3030 foot length of the bridge and then shuttle back to the center. The catwalk has been an existing structure of the bridge since its original construction, and Bridge Walk LLC saw an opportunity to give unique tours across the walkway. Creating Bridge Walk only required a simple shuttle system, improving the trail access, and installing an innovative safety system for guests making it impossible for tour guests to fall off the bridge.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Canyon Rim Visitor Center\r\n162 Visitor Center Rd.\r\nLansing, WV 25862\r\n<a href=\"http://bridgewalk.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Bridgewalk.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n<div><iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/embed?mid=zF2Ov4mSNUbs.k7huXt1Burjg\" width=\"460\" height=\"325\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<!-- end of col-container-cb -->',	'Adrenaline Junkie',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'206-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-07-02 13:28:53',	'2015-07-02 17:28:53',	'',	206,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/206-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
