(670,	2,	'2015-07-08 11:20:52',	'2015-07-08 15:20:52',	'<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\r\n<h4>Best Events</h4>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_287\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"210\"]<img class=\"wp-image-287\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/festivall_pic-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"festivall_pic\" width=\"210\" height=\"210\" /> Directional Signs from FestivAll[/caption]\r\n<h3>FestivAll</h3>\r\nThe event features visual arts, music, theater, dance and film as well as other cultural and entertainment events. It mixes fine arts and pop arts in venues and locations all over Charleston and includes a wide variety of styles and genres.\r\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\r\nAll year long Charleston has lots to offer the City Explorer. There\'s always something to do in the area!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-container-cb\">\r\n<h2>Charlestons diverse opportunities for entertainment, fun and learning makes it a great place to visit and to live! Heres a few ideas for the city explorer in all of us.</h2>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-1-cb\">\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/A-Map-Marker.png\" alt=\"A-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Clay Center for the Arts and       Sciences</h3>\r\nA 240,000 sq ft structure housing performing &amp; visual arts and sciences under one roof. Home to the Avampato Discovery Museum, Juliet Museum of Art and Maier Foundation Performance Hall.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">One Clay Square\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.theclaycenter.org/\" target=\"_blank\">theclaycenter.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/7-C-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Capitol Street</h3>\r\nThis bustling street serves as a main location for dining, learning and retail. Restaurants such as Ichiban, Pies and Pints, Adelphia, Graziano\'s Pizza and others line the streets, some offering outdoor dining.\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/7-E-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />ArtWalk</h3>\r\nA free self-guided walking tour of Downtown Charleston\'s shops, galleries and businesses featuring a variety of art - from paintings and sculptures to  photography and music. ArtWalk is held the third Thursday of each month.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\"><a href=\"http://www.artwalkcwv.com/\" target=\"_blank\">artwalkcwv.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/7-G-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Capitol Market</h3>\r\nBuilt from an 1800s railroad transfer dock, the market serves as an indoor/outdoor farmer\'s market, home of a variety of specialty shops and Sohos restaurant. The Charleston CVB also has a satellite site at the market.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">800 Smith Street\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.capitolmarket.net/\" target=\"_blank\">capitolmarket.net</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/7-B-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Live on the Levee</h3>\r\nAn outdoor concert series presented by the City of Charleston, WV. The concerts take place each Friday from Memorial Day Weekend to Labor Day Weekend.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Kanawha Blvd.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://liveontheleveecharleston.com\" target=\"_blank\">liveontheleveecharleston.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/7-D-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Bridge Road Shops</h3>\r\nUnique shops located in a charming neighborhood commercial district. Experience world class dining, shop for your favorite designer clothes, decorate your home with the warmth of one-of-a kind accessories, and experience local and regional art.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\"><a href=\"http://www.bridgeroad.org\" target=\"_blank\">bridgeroad.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/7-F-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Hale Street</h3>\r\nThis hidden street gem offers a unique group of stores and restaurants. Shop at Stray Dog Antiques, get pampered at Tops Off Barber Shop, Salon and Spa, get a smoothie at Mission Savvy Vegan Cafe and dinner at Celsius.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n<div><iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/embed?mid=zF2Ov4mSNUbs.kSaj6sWsDuA4\" width=\"460\" height=\"325\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>',	'City Explorer',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'187-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-07-08 11:20:52',	'2015-07-08 15:20:52',	'',	187,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/187-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(671,	2,	'2015-07-08 11:21:40',	'2015-07-08 15:21:40',	'<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\r\n<h4>Best Events for Families</h4>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_253\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"210\"]<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/FestivALL_2014_Childrens_Art_Fair_11_SMALLER_Sava_-__Javins_authorized.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-253\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/FestivALL_2014_Childrens_Art_Fair_11_SMALLER_Sava_-__Javins_authorized-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"FestivALL_2014_Childrens_Art_Fair_11_SMALLER_Sava_-__Javins_authorized\" width=\"210\" height=\"140\" /></a> Children\'s Art Fair.  Photo Courtesy of FestivAll.[/caption]\r\n<h3>Clay Center Family Fun Days</h3>\r\nEach day is full of family entertainment with themed science and art activities taking place throughout the day in addition to our three floors of art and science exhibits.\r\n<h3>Children\'s Art Fair and Kanawha County Public Library Street Fair</h3>\r\nA perfect combination for two days of family fun: Make &amp; take craft opportunities from invited artisans and groups, a sale of work by children and youth in Kanawha County neighborhood programs; a stage with child-friendly performances\r\n<h3>Movie Nights at Magic Island</h3>\r\nSponsored by local radio station, WQBE, Magic Island becomes a free, family friendly movie theater under the stars. The Island opens up at 6 with a Kids Zone &amp; the movie will start around dusk! Movie Nights take place Wednesday nights in June.\r\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\r\nAll year long there\'s plenty of Family Fun in Charleston, WV!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-container-cb\">\r\n<h2>Charleston is a great place for families!  With so many exciting kid-friendly activities including sports, arts and food, theres never a dull moment. For more ideas for family fun, check out our event calendar.</h2>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-1-cb\">\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/A-Map-Marker.png\" alt=\"A-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />WV Power</h3>\r\nMinor League baseball team in the South Atlantic League. The Class A Pittsburgh Pirates affiliate plays home games at Appalachian Power Park, also home to the WVSSAC baseball tournament.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Appalachian Power Park\r\n601 Morris St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://wvpower.com\" target=\"_blank\">wvpower.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/8-C-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Public Libraries</h3>\r\nOur local libraries are great places for fun and learning! Many events, programs &amp; services are free to the public. Kanawha County public library also provides geocaching equipment for rent.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Kanawha County Public Library\r\n123 Capitol St\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://kanawhalibrary.org/\" target=\"_blank\">kanawhalibrary.org</a></p>\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">South Charleston Public Library\r\n312 4th Avenue\r\nSouth Charleston WV 25303\r\n<a href=\"http://www.southcharlestonlibrary.org/\" target=\"_blank\">southcharlestonlibrary.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/8-e-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Chuck E Cheese</h3>\r\nLocated at Southridge Centre, Chuck E. Cheeses is a kid-centric experience. Admission is free and games require tokens that can be purchased. There\'s also a show consisting of characters &amp; music.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">2846 Mountaineer Blvd.\r\nCharleston, WV, 25309\r\n<a href=\"http://www.chuckecheese.com/\" target=\"_blank\">chuckecheese.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/8-G-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Waterways</h3>\r\nWaterways offers pool, tube &amp; body slides, lazy river, walking trail, unlimited putt-putt golf and kiddie island. Shelters available for family outings. Concession food is available for meals and snacks.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">109 Water Way\r\nAlkol, WV 25501\r\n<a href=\"http://waterwayspark.net/\" target=\"_blank\">waterwayspark.net</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/8-B-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Clay Center for the Arts and      Sciences</h3>\r\nA 240,000 sq ft structure housing performing &amp; visual arts and sciences under one roof. Home to the Avampato Discovery Museum, Juliet Museum of Art and Maier Foundation Performance\r\nHall.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">One Clay Square\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.theclaycenter.org/\" target=\"_blank\">theclaycenter.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/8-D-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />The Peanut Shoppe</h3>\r\nThe Peanut Shoppe has been a Charleston tradition for over 60 years. Established in 1950 by Delbert Moore, it is still in its original location. We recommend the chocolate stars!\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">126 Capitol St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/thepeanutshoppe\" target=\"_blank\">facebook.com/thepeanutshoppe</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/8-F-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Camden Park</h3>\r\nLooking for old-fashioned fun? Camden Park, WVs only amusement park, is a 26 acre park located near Huntington. Established in 1903, the park is home to more than thirty rides and attractions, including a full-size traditional wooden roller coaster and several other vintage rides.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">5000 Waverly Rd.\r\nHuntington, WV 25704\r\n<a href=\"http://www.camdenpark.com/\" target=\"_blank\">camdenpark.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/8-H-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Coonskin Park</h3>\r\nThe park includes over 1,000 acres of hiking/biking trails, an accessible 18 hole golf course, Olympic size pool, picnic shelters, tennis courts, horseshoe pits, playground, ampitheater,\r\nsoccer stadium and wedding garden.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">2000 Coonskin Drive\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\n<a href=\"http://www.kcprc.com/Parks/Coonskin-Park.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">Coonskin-Park</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n<div><iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/embed?mid=zF2Ov4mSNUbs.km_PDXqCqQi8\" width=\"460\" height=\"325\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>',	'Family Fun',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'202-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-07-08 11:21:40',	'2015-07-08 15:21:40',	'',	202,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/202-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
