"_blank\">chuckecheese.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/8-G-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Waterways</h3>\r\nWaterways offers pool, tube &amp; body slides, lazy river, walking trail, unlimited putt-putt golf and kiddie island. Shelters available for family outings. Concession food is available for meals and snacks.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">109 Water Way\r\nAlkol, WV 25501\r\n<a href=\"http://waterwayspark.net/\" target=\"_blank\">waterwayspark.net</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/8-B-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Clay Center for the Arts and      Sciences</h3>\r\nA 240,000 sq ft structure housing performing &amp; visual arts and sciences under one roof. Home to the Avampato Discovery Museum, Juliet Museum of Art and Maier Foundation Performance\r\nHall.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">One Clay Square\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.theclaycenter.org/\" target=\"_blank\">theclaycenter.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/8-D-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />The Peanut Shoppe</h3>\r\nThe Peanut Shoppe has been a Charleston tradition for over 60 years. Established in 1950 by Delbert Moore, it is still in its original location. We recommend the chocolate stars!\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">126 Capitol St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/thepeanutshoppe\" target=\"_blank\">facebook.com/thepeanutshoppe</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/8-F-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Camden Park</h3>\r\nLooking for old-fashioned fun? Camden Park, WVs only amusement park, is a 26 acre park located near Huntington. Established in 1903, the park is home to more than thirty rides and attractions, including a full-size traditional wooden roller coaster and several other vintage rides.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">5000 Waverly Rd.\r\nHuntington, WV 25704\r\n<a href=\"http://www.camdenpark.com/\" target=\"_blank\">camdenpark.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/8-H-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Coonskin Park</h3>\r\nThe park includes over 1,000 acres of hiking/biking trails, an accessible 18 hole golf course, Olympic size pool, picnic shelters, tennis courts, horseshoe pits, playground, ampitheater,\r\nsoccer stadium and wedding garden.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">2000 Coonskin Drive\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\n<a href=\"http://www.kcprc.com/Parks/Coonskin-Park.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">Coonskin-Park</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n<div><iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/embed?mid=zF2Ov4mSNUbs.km_PDXqCqQi8\" width=\"460\" height=\"325\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>',	'Family Fun',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'202-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-07-08 11:22:17',	'2015-07-08 15:22:17',	'',	202,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/202-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(673,	2,	'2015-07-08 11:23:29',	'2015-07-08 15:23:29',	'<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\r\n<h4>Best Events for Families</h4>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_253\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"210\"]<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/FestivALL_2014_Childrens_Art_Fair_11_SMALLER_Sava_-__Javins_authorized.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-253\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/FestivALL_2014_Childrens_Art_Fair_11_SMALLER_Sava_-__Javins_authorized-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"FestivALL_2014_Childrens_Art_Fair_11_SMALLER_Sava_-__Javins_authorized\" width=\"210\" height=\"140\" /></a> Children\'s Art Fair. Photo Credit: FestivAll[/caption]\r\n<h3>Clay Center Family Fun Days</h3>\r\nEach day is full of family entertainment with themed science and art activities taking place throughout the day in addition to our three floors of art and science exhibits.\r\n<h3>Children\'s Art Fair and Kanawha County Public Library Street Fair</h3>\r\nA perfect combination for two days of family fun: Make &amp; take craft opportunities from invited artisans and groups, a sale of work by children and youth in Kanawha County neighborhood programs; a stage with child-friendly performances\r\n<h3>Movie Nights at Magic Island</h3>\r\nSponsored by local radio station, WQBE, Magic Island becomes a free, family friendly movie theater under the stars. The Island opens up at 6 with a Kids Zone &amp; the movie will start around dusk! Movie Nights take place Wednesday nights in June.\r\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\r\nAll year long there\'s plenty of Family Fun in Charleston, WV!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-container-cb\">\r\n<h2>Charleston is a great place for families!  With so many exciting kid-friendly activities including sports, arts and food, theres never a dull moment. For more ideas for family fun, check out our event calendar.</h2>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-1-cb\">\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/A-Map-Marker.png\" alt=\"A-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />WV Power</h3>\r\nMinor League baseball team in the South Atlantic League. The Class A Pittsburgh Pirates affiliate plays home games at Appalachian Power Park, also home to the WVSSAC baseball tournament.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Appalachian Power Park\r\n601 Morris St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://wvpower.com\" target=\"_blank\">wvpower.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/8-C-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Public Libraries</h3>\r\nOur local libraries are great places for fun and learning! Many events, programs &amp; services are free to the public. Kanawha County public library also provides geocaching equipment for rent.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Kanawha County Public Library\r\n123 Capitol St\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://kanawhalibrary.org/\" target=\"_blank\">kanawhalibrary.org</a></p>\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">South Charleston Public Library\r\n312 4th Avenue\r\nSouth Charleston WV 25303\r\n<a href=\"http://www.southcharlestonlibrary.org/\" target=\"_blank\">southcharlestonlibrary.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/8-e-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Chuck E Cheese</h3>\r\nLocated at Southridge Centre, Chuck E. Cheeses is a kid-centric experience. Admission is free and games require tokens that can be purchased. There\'s also a show consisting of characters &amp; music.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">2846 Mountaineer Blvd.\r\nCharleston, WV, 25309\r\n<a href=\"http://www.chuckecheese.com/\" target=\"_blank\">chuckecheese.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/8-G-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Waterways</h3>\r\nWaterways offers pool, tube &amp; body slides, lazy river, walking trail, unlimited putt-putt golf and kiddie island. Shelters available for family outings. Concession food is available for meals and snacks.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">109 Water Way\r\nAlkol, WV 25501\r\n<a href=\"http://waterwayspark.net/\" target=\"_blank\">waterwayspark.net</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/8-B-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Clay Center for the Arts and      Sciences</h3>\r\nA 240,000 sq ft structure housing performing &amp; visual arts and sciences under one roof. Home to the Avampato Discovery Museum, Juliet Museum of Art and Maier Foundation Performance\r\nHall.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">One Clay Square\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.theclaycenter.org/\" target=\"_blank\">theclaycenter.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/8-D-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />The Peanut Shoppe</h3>\r\nThe Peanut Shoppe has been a Charleston tradition for over 60 years. Established in 1950 by Delbert Moore, it is still in its original location. We recommend the chocolate stars!\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">126 Capitol St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/thepeanutshoppe\" target=\"_blank\">facebook.com/thepeanutshoppe</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/8-F-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Camden Park</h3>\r\nLooking for old-fashioned fun? Camden Park, WVs only amusement park, is a 26 acre park located near Huntington. Established in 1903, the park is home to more than thirty rides and attractions, including a full-size traditional wooden roller coaster and several other vintage rides.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">5000 Waverly Rd.\r\nHuntington, WV 25704\r\n<a href=\"http://www.camdenpark.com/\" target=\"_blank\">camdenpark.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/8-H-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Coonskin Park</h3>\r\nThe park includes over 1,000 acres of hiking/biking trails, an accessible 18 hole golf course, Olympic size pool, picnic shelters, tennis courts, horseshoe pits, playground, ampitheater,\r\nsoccer stadium and wedding garden.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">2000 Coonskin Drive\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\n<a href=\"http://www.kcprc.com/Parks/Coonskin-Park.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">Coonskin-Park</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n<div><iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/embed?mid=zF2Ov4mSNUbs.km_PDXqCqQi8\" width=\"460\" height=\"325\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>',	'Family Fun',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'202-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-07-08 11:23:29',	'2015-07-08 15:23:29',	'',	202,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/202-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(674,	2,	'2015-07-08 11:24:20',	'2015-07-08 15:24:20',	'<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\r\n<h4>Best Events for the Foodie</h4>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_360\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"210\"]<img class=\"wp-image-360\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/taste_of_all1-300x230.jpg\" alt=\"taste_of_all1\" width=\"210\" height=\"161\" /> Taste-of-All. Photo Credit: FestivAll[/caption]\r\n<h3>Smoke on the Water Chili Cookoff</h3>\r\nChili cooks compete to see who has the best red, green and home-style chili and salsa. Kids activities, frozen t-shirt and hot pepper eating contests, live music, local food vendors and plenty of cold drinks. Proceeds benefit HospiceCare.\r\n<h3>Mac and Cheese Cookoff</h3>\r\nMac and Cheese enthusiasts enter and taste the Charleston area\'s best Macaroni and Cheese. Proceeds benefit the Childhood Language Center of Charleston, WV.\r\n<h3>Taste-of-All</h3>\r\nTaste-of-All Charleston is a tour of the culinary talents and amazing cuisine available throughout Charleston, WV. Fun for the whole family, visitors can taste amazing dishes served by some of\r\nthe gifted chefs and restaurants from the valley.\r\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\r\nSpring, summer and fall are perfect for outdoor dining but all year-round is great for those special Charleston places that love to serve you!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-container-cb\">\r\n<h2>You dont have to look very far to find great cuisine in Charleston! We have highlighted just a few of the amazing places you can go to have a casual meal, a quick bite, a fancy feast or make your own!</h2>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-1-cb\">\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-463\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/A-Map-Marker.png\" alt=\"A-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Bluegrass Kitchen</h3>\r\nFarm-to-table comfort food with a modern edge. Specialties are vegetarian &amp; omnivorous dishes made from ingredients naturally sourced within WV and the Appalachians served in a dining room restored to its circa 1920\'s beauty.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">1600 Washington St E\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\n<a href=\"http://www.bluegrasswv.com/\" target=\"_blank\">bluegrasswv.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-463\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-C-Marker.png\" alt=\"A-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Charleston Bread Company</h3>\r\nBreads, cookies, pastries and more baked fresh every day.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">601 Capitol St.\r\nCharleston, West Virginia 25301</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-463\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-E-Marker.png\" alt=\"A-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />The Block</h3>\r\nThe Block offers cocktails and small bites complimented by views of downtown Capitol St. The restaurant features an active cheese cave and glass enclosed wine cellar. Jazz music on selected nights.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">201 Capitol St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.theblockwv.com/\" target=\"_blank\">theblockwv.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-463\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-G-Marker.png\" alt=\"A-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Capitol Market</h3>\r\nBuilt from an 1800s railroad transfer dock, the market serves as an indoor/outdoor farmer\'s market, home of a variety of specialty shops and Sohos restaurant. The Charleston CVB also has a satellite site at the market.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">800 Smith Street\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.capitolmarket.net/\" target=\"_blank\">capitolmarket.net</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-463\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-I-Marker.png\" alt=\"A-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />JQ Dickenson Salt Works</h3>\r\nDescendants of the original salt makers in the Kanawha Valley produce clean, artisinal salt, harvested by hand. Tours are available with reservations.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">371 Kanawha Salines Dr.\r\nMalden, WV 25306\r\n<a href=\"http://www.jqdsalt.com/\" target=\"_blank\">jqdsalt.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-463\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-B-Marker.png\" alt=\"A-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Black Sheep Burritos</h3>\r\nLocated in the heart of downtown, Black Sheep offers an eclectic mix of tex-mex menu items and Charleston Brewing Company beer. One of the best brunch menus in the Kanawha Valley.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">702 Quarrier St,\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.blacksheepwv.com/\" target=\"_blank\">blacksheepwv.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-463\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-D-Marker.png\" alt=\"A-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Ellen\'s Ice Cream</h3>\r\nEllens Homemade Ice Cream was born over 15 years ago with the simple mission to delight customers with all-natural, high-quality ingredients and a welcoming and comfortable atmosphere.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">225 Capitol St,\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://ellensicecream.com/\" target=\"_blank\">ellensicecream.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-463\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-F-Marker.png\" alt=\"A-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />West Side Farmers Market</h3>\r\nThe purpose and mission of the market is to educate about local food resources and to revitalize the community by creating a vibrant market at which local farmers and home gardeners may sell their produce.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">303 Washington St. West\r\nCharleston, WV 25302\r\n<a href=\"http://wsfmcharleston.com/\" target=\"_blank\">wsfmcharleston.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-463\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-H-Marker.png\" alt=\"A-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Butter it Up!</h3>\r\nEver had butter in your coffee? This is a must-try. Butter it up! is a gluten free coffee shop. They offer paleoish breakfast, lunch, and dinner options in addition to local products.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">714 Virginia St E,\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/butteritupcrw\" target=\"_blank\">facebook.com/butteritupcrw</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n<div><iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/embed?mid=zF2Ov4mSNUbs.kJ6jMMcM14rs\" width=\"460\" height=\"325\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>',	'Foodie',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'189-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-07-08 11:24:20',	'2015-07-08 15:24:20',	'',	189,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/189-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(675,	2,	'2015-07-08 11:24:54',	'2015-07-08 15:24:54',	'<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\r\n<h4>Best Events for History</h4>\r\n<h4><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-367\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/capitol_night_-shutter-1-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"capitol_night_-shutter (1)\" width=\"210\" height=\"140\" /></h4>\r\n<h3>Battle of Scary Creek/Skirmish at Hurricane Bridge - Civil War Reenactment</h3>\r\nPart of a Civil War weekend in Hurricane, the event commemorates two engagements of the Civil War separated by a space of two years. The Battle of Scary Creek., July 17, 1861 and the Blue and Gray Skirmish at Hurricane Bridge, March 28, 1863. Also, enjoy crafts, sutler\'s row, storytelling, a night firing, parade drills, a ladies tea, a historical lantern tour and a military dance.\r\n<h3>WV Day Celebrations</h3>\r\nCelebrate West Virginia\'s birthday with a variety of activities on the grounds of the WV State Capitol.\r\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\r\nHistory is happening every day of the year and this is certainly the case for those wanting to learn more about Charleston and West Virginia\'s history.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-container-cb\">\r\n<h2>Charlestons diverse opportunities for entertainment, fun and learning makes it a great place to visit and to live! Heres a few ideas for the city explorer in all of us.</h2>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-1-cb\">\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/A-Map-Marker.png\" alt=\"A-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />WV State Museum</h3>\r\nThis free-to-the-public museum offers an interactive look into the history, culture and treasures of West Virginia. The museum is designed as a timeline telling story of WV. A museum gift shop offers WV locally-made products.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">WV Division of Culture and History\r\nCapitol Complex\r\n1900 Kanawha Boulevard East\r\nCharleston WV 25305\r\n<a href=\"http://www.wvculture.org/museum/State-Museum-Index.html\" target=\"_blank\">WV-State-Museum</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-C-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />WV Humanities Council</h3>\r\nThe Council provides constant events and programs promoting the Mountain State and it\'s art, literature and history. It is located at the MacFarland-Hubbard House, which is listed on the National Register of Historic Places.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">1310 Kanawha Blvd., E.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.wvhumanities.org/\" target=\"_blank\">wvhumanities.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-E-Marker.png\" alt=\"E-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Malden</h3>\r\nHistoric town just east of Charleston. VIsit Booker T. Washington\'s childhood home, African Zion Baptist Church, J.Q. Dickenson Salt and many other historic buildings and sites.\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-G-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Governors Mansion</h3>\r\nTours of the Governor\'s Mansion begin on the front porch of the Mansion on Thursdays and Fridays. Reservations are required and are honored on a first-come, first-serve basis. Call for reservations at 304-558-4839.\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-H-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />West Virginia State Capitol</h3>\r\nTours begin on the first floor Rotunda. Groups under 10 are welcome to join a regularly scheduled tour without reservations. Groups of more than 10 are best served with a reservation and tours of Senate/Representatives chamber require reservations. 304-558-2601\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-B-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Craik-Patton House</h3>\r\nCraik-Patton House was built about 1834 in the Greek Revival style. It is open for tours from April through October. It is listed on the National Register of Historic Places since 1970.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">2809 Kanawha Blvd. E.\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\n<a href=\"http://www.craik-patton.org/\" target=\"_blank\">craik-patton.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-D-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Coal Heritage Trail</h3>\r\nA driving trail that winds through over 187 rugged miles of scenic industrial heritage. You will pass through National Historic Districts and the physical remnants of the coal boom such as coal miners\' homes, company stores, company offices and more.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">100 Kelly Avenue\r\nOak Hill, WV 25901\r\n<a href=\"http://www.coalheritage.org\" target=\"_blank\">coalheritage.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-F-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Blenko Glass</h3>\r\nFor over 100 years, Blenko has maintained the tradition of hand making glassware in America. They offer a wide range of products which include functional glassware, art glass, mouth blown sheet glass, dalle de verre and other quality products. Tours are available.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">9 Bill Blenko Drive\r\nMilton, WV 25541\r\n<a href=\"http://www.blenko.com/\" target=\"_blank\">blenko.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-I-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Kanawha Blvd. Historical            Markers</h3>\r\nAs you stroll along the riverbank, you will come across a series of historic markers commemorating moments in West Virginia history. These markers are part of the over 1,000 markers throughout the state marking sites of significance.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n<div><iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/embed?mid=zF2Ov4mSNUbs.kIo4W4VDDTqM\" width=\"460\" height=\"325\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>',	'History Buff',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'191-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-07-08 11:24:54',	'2015-07-08 15:24:54',	'',	191,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/191-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(676,	2,	'2015-07-08 11:33:35',	'2015-07-08 15:33:35',	'<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\n<h4>Best Events for Music Lovers</h4>\n<h3>Vandalia Gathering</h3>\nThe Vandalia Gathering brings together the finest traditional Appalachian musicians for a weekend of great picking. Elder statesmen and young upstarts perform on stage, compete in contests and play in impromptu jam sessions all over the Capitol Complex. Visitors to the Gathering can enjoy fiddle, banjo, mandolin and guitar contests outside during the day, and concerts in the State Theater in the evenings. Food and craft vendors are also part of the festival.\n<h3>Symphony Sunday</h3>\nFree day of music with the WV Symphony Orchestra and other musicians on the lawn of the University of Charleston. Artisan tents and food vendors are also present throughout the day. The day ends with the Symphony playing and fireworks.\n<h3>Wine &amp; All That Jazz Festival</h3>\nPart of FestivAll, Charlestons Fund for the Arts produces this day long concert and lawn party. West Virginia wineries sell glasses and bottles of a variety of wines, jazz musicians take the stage and attendees enjoy the lawn of the University of Charleston.\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\nSummer is a music lover\'s paradise in the Charleston area. With a large variety of outdoor concerts and events, there\'s always an opportunity to enjoy the sweet sounds of summer in Charlie West.\n\n</div>\n<div class=\"content-block col-container-cb\">\n<h2>The music of the Charleston area is a diverse and eclectic mix, sure to please the ears of all looking for some great tunes. Live performances are abundant in the area at small and large venues as well as a variety of special events.</h2>\n<div class=\"content-block col-1-cb\">\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/A-Map-Marker.png\" alt=\"A-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Empty Glass</h3>\nLocated under a 3-story house jacked up in the air in Charlestons historically diverse East End. Here you will find delicious food, great conversation, friendly spirits and live original music from all over the planet.\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">410 Elizabeth St.\nCharleston, WV 25311\n<a href=\"http://www.emptyglass.com\" target=\"_blank\">emptyglass.com</a></p>\n\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-C-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Mountain Stage</h3>\nFor over 30 years \"Mountain Stage w/ Larry Groce\" has been the home of live music on public radio. Founded in 1983 in Charleston, WV and is produced by West Virginia Public Radio the show travels but most are recorded at the WV State Capitol Complex.\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Culture Center Theater\nCapitol Complex\n1900 Kanawha Boulevard East\nCharleston WV 25305\n<a href=\"http://www.mountainstage.org\" target=\"_blank\">mountainstage.org</a></p>\n\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-F-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Taylor Books</h3>\nIn addition to an open mic night and scheduled performances, they have a broad selection of books, wide variety of hard-to-find magazines and unique collection of cards and gifts as well as an Art Annex.\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">226 Capitol St.\nCharleston, WV 25301\n<a href=\"http://www.taylorbooks.com\" target=\"_blank\">taylorbooks.com</a></p>\n&nbsp;\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-H-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />WV Symphony Orchestra</h3>\nThe West Virginia Symphony Orchestra presents classical, pops, family &amp; chamber-music concerts annually. The WVSO also provides affordable, high-quality concerts, collaborations with arts organizations and a nationally award-winning education program.\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">One Clay Square\nCharleston, WV 25301\n<a href=\"http://wvsymphony.org\" target=\"_blank\">wvsymphony.org</a></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-B-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Live on the Levee</h3>\nAn outdoor concert series presented by the City of Charleston, WV. The concerts take place each Friday from Memorial Day Weekend to Labor Day Weekend.\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Kanawha Blvd.\nCharleston, WV 25301\n<a href=\"http://liveontheleveecharleston.com\" target=\"_blank\">liveontheleveecharleston.com</a></p>\n\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-D-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Brown Bag Concerts</h3>\nFree Lunchtime Concerts in Davis Park the third Wednesday of the month from May until September. The concerts last from 11:30am to 1:30pm.\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Davis Park\nCharleston, WV 25301</p>\n\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-E-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Fret and Fiddle</h3>\nFret \'n Fiddle offers new and used string instruments. Specializing in vintage instruments, including guitars, mandolins, banjos and fiddles. They also offer consigned merchandise and a recording studio.\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">809 Pennsylvania Ave.\nSt Albans, WV 25177\n<a href=\"http://www.fretnfiddle.com\" target=\"_blank\">fretnfiddle.com</a></p>\n\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-G-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Sullivan\'s Records</h3>\nCharleston\'s newest record store! They specialize in vinyl, with thousands of new &amp; used records in stock, as well as tons of CD\'s, DVD\'s, and more.\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">1588-A Washington St E,\nCharleston, WV 25311\n<a href=\"http://sullivansrecords.com/\" target=\"_blank\">sullivansrecords.com</a></p>\n\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-I-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />WV Music Hall of Fame</h3>\nThe WV Music Hall of Fame has a satellite exhibit in the Dickinson Street parking. The display features instruments, photos, posters and vintage memorabilia from Mountain Stage musicians  with an emphasis on those from the Kanawha Valley.\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Quarrier and Dickenson Sts.\nCharleston, WV 25301\n<a href=\"http://www.wvmusichalloffame.com/\" target=\"_blank\">www.wvmusichalloffame.com</a></p>\n\n</div>\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\n<div><iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/embed?mid=zF2Ov4mSNUbs.kOJvQgaood6w\" width=\"460\" height=\"325\"></iframe></div>\n</div>',	'Music Lover',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'196-autosave-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-07-08 11:33:35',	'2015-07-08 15:33:35',	'',	196,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/196-autosave-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
