(685,	2,	'2015-07-08 11:34:34',	'2015-07-08 15:34:34',	'<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\r\n<h4>Best Events</h4>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_294\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"210\"]<img class=\"wp-image-294\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/live_on_levee1-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"live_on_levee1\" width=\"210\" height=\"210\" /> Live on the Levee. Photo Credit: Megan Tarbett[/caption]\r\n<h3>Live On The Levee</h3>\r\nOutdoor concert series presented by the City of Charleston, WV. The concerts take place each Friday from Memorial Day Weekend to Labor Day Weekend.\r\n<h3>East End Pub Crawl</h3>\r\nJoin in on the St. Patrick\'s Day fun on the East End of Charleston.  Live, local Celtic music from FOOTMAD, walk from bar to bar (over 10) enjoying drink specials and look for the hidden shamrocks throughout the area in order to win big!\r\n<h3>Boo Bash</h3>\r\nAll the ghosts and goblins come out to play at this traditional-style Halloween party.  Dance the night away with the event\'s DJ and enjoy great food and drinks, games and a photo booth. Hosted by the South Charleston Chamber of Commerce, its a fun-filled fright night!\r\n<h3>HallowEast</h3>\r\nIf you\'re looking for a spooky time, HallowEast has lots of events to make your Halloween. ArtMares, Main Street Murder Mystery, East End Zombie Walk, Run Like Hell Zombie 5K and the Costume Crawl are all exciting events that make this week of scary a truly ghouly experience.\r\n<h3>Murder Mysteries</h3>\r\nThese exciting Who-Dun-It events are sure to entertain the best of detectives.  Located at the Comedy Zone in the Holiday Inn &amp; Suites, participants enjoy a buffet dinner and an entertaining interactive show with a different theme each time.\r\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\r\nThere\'s always time to party!  But if you\'re looking for great times with special events, look around the holidays...particularly St. Patty\'s Day and  Halloween!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-container-cb\">\r\n<h2>Whether you want fast-paced excitement, great music or a low-key culinary experience, theres always something to do late-night in Charleston!</h2>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-1-cb\">\r\n<h3>Comedy Zone</h3>\r\nTwo of the nation\'s funniest comedians travel to Charleston to entertain the crowds. Full food and drink menus available during the show. Shows are Fridays at 8pm &amp; Saturdays at 7pm and 9pm.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">400 2nd Ave.\r\nCharleston, WV 25303\r\n<a href=\"http://comedyzonecharleston.com\" target=\"_blank\">comedyzonecharleston.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Capitol Street Nightlife</h3>\r\nCapitol Street &amp; adjacent Kanawha Blvd. have a variety of bars/lounges for all scenes. Whether youre looking for a great glass of wine, sports bar, irish pub or game of pool, its all here!\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Capitol St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Bricks and Barrels</h3>\r\nIf you\'re looking for an upscale evening, Bricks and Barrels is the place. Sit in one of the Barrel shaped booths and enjoy their large variety of beers and wines along with their eclectic menu.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">1214 Smith St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.bricksnbarrels.com/\" target=\"_blank\">bricksnbarrels.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Empty Glass</h3>\r\nLocated under a 3-story house jacked up in the air in Charlestons historically diverse East End. Here you will find delicious food, great conversation, friendly spirits and live original music.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">410 Elizabeth St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25311</p>\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\"><a href=\"http://www.emptyglass.com\" target=\"_blank\">emptyglass.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3>Celsius</h3>\r\nAn upscale lounge serving wine, craft beers and specialty cocktails. The food menu includes burgers, salads, flat breads and a unique variety of dishes.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">212 Hale St\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/CelsiusWV\" target=\"_blank\">facebook.com/CelsiusWV</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Timothy\'s</h3>\r\nTimothys is located directly below the Quarrier Diner. Watch your favorite sports on any one of the 17 high definition flat screens. They are constantly hosting events from live music, trivia nights and more.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">1022 Quarrier St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.timothyssportsbar.com/\" target=\"_blank\">timothyssportsbar.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Mardi Gras Casino</h3>\r\nOver 90,000 square feet of gaming space, the Mardi Gras Casino offers over 30 table games, over 1,000 slot machines, greyhound racing, restaurants and bars and much more!\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">#1 Greyhound Drive\r\nCross Lanes, WV 25313\r\n<a href=\"http://www.mardigrascasinowv.com/\" target=\"_blank\">mardigrascasinowv.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n<div>placeholder for map</div>\r\n</div>',	'Night Owl',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'200-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-07-08 11:34:34',	'2015-07-08 15:34:34',	'',	200,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/200-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(686,	2,	'2015-07-08 11:35:06',	'2015-07-08 15:35:06',	'<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\r\n<h4>Best Events</h4>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_297\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"210\"]<img class=\"wp-image-297\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/shutterstock_173318291-300x191.jpg\" alt=\"BBall through hoop\" width=\"210\" height=\"134\" /> WVSSAC Basketball Tournament[/caption]\r\n<h3>Annual Charleston Public Courts Tennis Tournament</h3>\r\nJuly 10-18, 2015\r\n\r\nLargest annual tennis tournament in Charleston. The public courts tournament matches take place at Schoenbaum Tennis Complex, Tennis Indoor Center and Charleston Catholic High\r\nSchool Sports Complex. rain sites include tennis indoor center, YMCA and the Charleston Tennis Club.\r\n<h3>WVSSAC Tournaments</h3>\r\nThe West Virginia Secondary School Athletic Commission (WVSSAC) hold their annual high school boys basketball, girls basketball, volleyball, baseball, tennis and track and field state\r\ntournaments in the Charleston area throughout the year.\r\n\r\nBoys Basketball - March\r\nGirls Basketball - March\r\nVolleyball - November\r\nBaseball - June\r\nTennis - April\r\nTrack and Field - April\r\n<h3>Sportsfest Meets WV Games</h3>\r\nSportsFEST includes the Jet Ski Hyrdo-Turf National Championship and the EVP Pro Am Beach Championship. WV Games, the largest collection of sanctioned sporting events in West Virginia, includes events such as a cornhole tournament, crossfit, tabata bootcamp, slalom skateboarding, wrestling, Jiu Jitsu and the West Virginia Storm will be stunting and tumbling. In total, more than 400 professional athletes will compete this weekend.\r\n<h3>Capital City Challenge</h3>\r\nSeptember 19, 2015\r\n\r\n4.2 mile Run, 4.2 mile Row, 16.8 mile Ride\r\n\r\nRun, Row &amp; Ride through the capital city on this flat, fast course that showcases the beauty of downtown Charleston. This unique yet competitive event is designed for competitors of all fitness and skill levels. This family-friendly challenge features a post-race picnic with music, kids\' activities, and great prizes. Solo and team entries are welcome.\r\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\r\nThere\'s always opportunities to watch and participate in sports in the Charleston area! Outdoor events are primarily available in late spring to early fall.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-container-cb\">\r\n<h2>Theres a lot of great competition in Charleston! Whether youre a spectator or a competitor,check out these great opportunities in all kinds of different sports.</h2>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-1-cb\">\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/A-Map-Marker.png\" alt=\"A-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />WV Power</h3>\r\nMinor League baseball team in the South Atlantic League. The Class A Pittsburgh Pirates affiliate plays home games at Appalachian Power Park, also home to the WVSSAC baseball tournament.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Appalachian Power Park\r\n601 Morris St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://wvpower.com\" target=\"_blank\">wvpower.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-C-Marker.png\" alt=\"C-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />WV Chaos</h3>\r\nFounded in 2003, WV Chaos plays in the USL Premier Development League (PDL), the 4th tier of the American Soccer Pyramid, in the South Atlantic Division of the Eastern Conference.\r\n\r\nSchoenbaum Soccer Complex\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">2000 Coonskin Dr.\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\n<a href=\"http://westvirginiachaossoccer.com\" target=\"_blank\">westvirginiachaossoccer.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-E-Marker.png\" alt=\"E-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />University of Charleston            Athletics</h3>\r\nThe UC Golden Eagles teams consist of baseball, basketball, cross country, football, golf ,soccer, tennis, track and field, volleyball, cheerleading, rowing, lacrosse and softball.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">University of Charleston\r\n2300 MacCorkle Ave., SE\r\nCharleston, WV 25304</p>\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">UC Stadium - Laidley Field\r\n200 Elizabeth St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\n<a href=\"http://ucgoldeneagles.com\" target=\"_blank\">ucgoldeneagles.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-G-Marker.png\" alt=\"G-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />West Virginia State                        University Athletics</h3>\r\nThe WVSU Yellow Jackets teams consist of baseball, basketball, football, golf, tennis, softball, cross country and volleyball.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">500 Fairlawn Ave.\r\nInstitute, WV 25112\r\n<a href=\"http://www.wvsuyellowjackets.com\" target=\"_blank\">wvsuyellowjackets.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-B-Marker.png\" alt=\"B-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Charleston Civic Center</h3>\r\nHosts a variety of annual sporting events including WVSSAC Boys and Girls Basketball State Tournaments, archery and volleyball tournaments, Mountain East Conference Championships, boxing/martial arts events, Capital Classic between WVU and Marshall Men\'s Basketball.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">200 Civic Center Dr.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.charlestonwvciviccenter.com\" target=\"_blank\">charlestonwvciviccenter.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-D-Marker.png\" alt=\"D-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Trace Fork Soccer Complex</h3>\r\nThe Friends of Coal Fields At Trace Fork Soccer Complex is a six field soccer complex is located at the Shops at Trace Fork, just off U.S. Rt. 119 south of Charleston, West Virginia.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">25 RHL Blvd.\r\nSouth Charleston, WV 25309\r\n<a href=\"http://traceforksoccer.com/\" target=\"_blank\">traceforksoccer.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-F-Marker.png\" alt=\"A-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Adelphia Sports Bar and              Grille</h3>\r\nVoted best appetizer and wings in the valley three years in a row! Adelphia infuses Greek and American cuisine to offer some of the best food around. Open 365 days a year and full menu served until midnight and later.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">218 Capitol Street\r\nCharleston WV, 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://adelphiasportsbar.com/\" target=\"_blank\">http://adelphiasportsbar.com/</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-H-Marker.png\" alt=\"A-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />South Charleston Memorial         Ice Arena</h3>\r\nNewly opened, state-of-the-art facility with amenities like an arcade and heated seating area that will accommodate 500 spectators. Groups of all sizes are welcome.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">20 RHL Blvd.\r\nCharleston, WV 25309\r\n<a href=\"http://cityofsouthcharleston.com/memorial-ice-arena/\" target=\"_blank\">memorial-ice-arena/</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\" size-full wp-image-463 alignnone\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/9-I-Marker.png\" alt=\"A-Map-Marker\" width=\"20\" height=\"31\" />Little Creek Park</h3>\r\nThe park has five baseball/softball fields, seven soccer fields, a football field, two tennis courts and two basketball courts. Also, 18-hold disc golf course and soap box derby track are located at the park.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">1 Little Creek Park Rd.\r\nSouth Charleston, WV 25309\r\n<a href=\"http://cityofsouthcharleston.com/little-creek-park/\" target=\"_blank\">little-creek-park/</a></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n<div><iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/embed?mid=zF2Ov4mSNUbs.kjg5elzGTzXs\" width=\"460\" height=\"325\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>',	'Sports Fan',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'194-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-07-08 11:35:06',	'2015-07-08 15:35:06',	'',	194,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/194-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
