(930,	3,	'2015-07-17 10:24:16',	'2015-07-17 14:24:16',	'<h2>National Alternative Fuels Training Consortium (NAFTC)</h2>\r\n<div class=\"note\">\r\n\r\nThe National Alternative Fuels Training Consortium (NAFTC) is a pioneer and national leader in developing, managing, and promoting programs and activities that desire to cure Americas addiction to oil, lead to energy independence, and encourage the greater use of cleaner transportation. The NAFTC is the only nationwide alternative fuel vehicle and advanced technology vehicle training organization in the United States. It is our mission to provide the training infrastructure for implementing widespread use of alternative fuels, alternative fuel vehicles (AFVs), and advanced technology vehicles, in an effort to increase our nations energy security and improve our air quality by reducing greenhouse gas emissions from our transportation system.\r\n\r\nThe NAFTC is headquartered at West Virginia University and conducts business under the auspices of the National Research Center for Coal and Energy. The NAFTC headquarters and the National Alternative Fuels Training Laboratory are located in Morgantown, West Virginia.\r\n\r\n</div>',	'National Alternative Fuels Training Consortium (NAFTC)',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'national-alternative-fuels-training-consortium-naftc',	'',	'',	'2015-07-17 10:24:16',	'2015-07-17 14:24:16',	'',	0,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/?post_type=chronosly_organizer&#038;p=930',	0,	'chronosly_organizer',	'',	0),
(932,	3,	'2015-07-17 10:26:26',	'2015-07-17 14:26:26',	'<strong>FREE Natural Gas and Propane Fleet Workshop</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Learn about the benefits of natural gas or propane conversion and how to prepare your shop.</strong>\r\n\r\nTake advantage of this FREE Natural Gas and Propane Fleet Workshop\r\n\r\nEVENT AGENDA (8:30 a.m. - 1:30 p.m.)\r\n\r\nWelcome and Introductions - 8:30 a.m. - 8:45 a.m.\r\nBill Davis, NAFTC Director\r\nKelly Bragg, West Virginia Clean State Program Co-Coordinator\r\n\r\nOverview of Gaseous Fuel Vehicles (Natural Gas and Propane) - 8:45 a.m. - 9:00 a.m.\r\nBill Davis, NAFTC Director\r\n\r\nGaseous Fuel Vehicles (Natural Gas and Propane) Fleet Perspective - 9:00 a.m. - 9:15 a.m.\r\nJudy Moore, NAFTC Assistant Director - Communications and Outreach\r\n\r\nPrepping Your Shop for Gaseous Fuels - 9:15 a.m. - 10:45 a.m.\r\nAdapting Your Facilities to Accommodate Gaseous Fuel Vehicles, Bill Davis, NAFTC Director\r\nApplicable Codes and Standards, Laws, Incentives, and More, WV Fire Marshal Office (Invited)\r\nHow and Why Ryder Converted to Natural Gas, Rueben Stokes, Ryder System, Inc. Director of Business Development - Advanced Fuels/Fleet Management Solutions\r\n\r\nBreak - 10:45 a.m. - 11:00 a.m.\r\n\r\nRoundtable Discussion - 11:00 a.m. - 11:45 a.m.\r\nKelly Bragg, West Virginia Clean State Program Co-Coordinator\r\nBill Davis, NAFTC Director\r\nTJ Meadows, CNG Business Development Manager, IGS Energy/CNG Services\r\nBret Chandler, Managing Director, Propane Fuel Technologies (Invited)\r\nJudy Moore, NAFTC Assistant Director - Communications and Outreach (Moderator)\r\n\r\nLUNCH AND DISCUSSION\r\nIn Meeting Room - 11:45 a.m. - 12:30 p.m.\r\n\r\nRYDER FACILITY TOUR\r\nTravel to Ryder Facility - 12:30 p.m. - 12:45 p.m.\r\nTour of Ryder Facility and Discussion - 12:45 p.m. - 1:30 p.m., Gene Harpold, Bluegrass Business Unit/Ryder System, Inc. Director, Sales\r\n\r\nCourses are offered through the National Alternative Fuels Training Consortium in Morgantown, WV. Customized classes can be brought to your location and are designed to meet your particular needs. Please contact micheal.smyth@mail.wvu.edu for customized training details, course pricing, and for NAFTC membership information.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;',	'FREE Natural Gas and Propane Fleet Workshop',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'free-natural-gas-and-propane-fleet-workshop',	'',	'',	'2015-07-17 10:35:15',	'2015-07-17 14:35:15',	'',	0,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/?post_type=chronosly&#038;p=932',	0,	'chronosly',	'',	0),
