(1173,	2,	'2015-07-23 22:44:05',	'2015-07-24 02:44:05',	'Celebrate the longstanding relationship between math and art with prints, paintings and sculptures from the Clay Centers collection. Examine how artists intentionally and intuitively use mathematical concepts like shape, pattern, symmetry and proportion to guide their creativity. Try it yourself when you solve puzzles and build geometric structures in an exhibit that challenges your mind.',	'ART EXHIBIT: MATH + ART',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'art-exhibit-math-art-20',	'',	'',	'2015-07-23 22:44:05',	'2015-07-24 02:44:05',	'',	0,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/?post_type=chronosly&#038;p=1173',	0,	'chronosly',	'',	0),
(1175,	2,	'2015-07-23 22:47:00',	'2015-07-24 02:47:00',	'A broad variety of time-tested and peer-reviewed painters from across the country (Scott Christensen, Quang Ho, etc.) have been invited to share three paintings each, during a week-long exhibition and sale at The Greenbrier Resort in White Sulphur Springs, WV.  Artists in attendance will be presenting talks and painting demonstrations which are complimentary and open to the public - as well as entertaining and educational.  Special guests, Troy Linger (publisher Art &amp; Antiques magazine) and John Dorfman (editor Art &amp; Antiques magazine) join us for Oct 24 and 25.  During 2015, several of the invited artists have been making their way to the area to paint images of landscapes we know.  We expect to have over 100 paintings in the exhibition.  The roster of artists continues to grow as we look to fill in any gaps - in figure, still-life, landscape, and style of painting - with quality work by national-award-winning artists.  Please come to the website, http://www.wallsgallery.com/greenbrierinvitational/ , to get to know the artists and their work and for more and updated event information.',	'The Greenbrier invitational',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'the-greenbrier-invitational',	'',	'',	'2015-08-04 12:44:40',	'2015-08-04 16:44:40',	'',	0,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/?post_type=chronosly&#038;p=1175',	0,	'chronosly',	'',	0),
