ost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/DC_Button_7-C.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />Capitol Street</h3>\r\nThis bustling street serves as a main location for dining, learning and retail. Restaurants such as Ichiban, Pies and Pints, Adelphia, Graziano\'s Pizza and others line the streets, some offering outdoor dining.<br /><br />\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/see-do/city-explorer\" target=\"_blank\"><button style=\"font-family: \'roboto_slabbold\';\">SHARE</button></a>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1244 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/DC_Button_7-E.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />ArtWalk</h3>\r\nA free self-guided walking tour of Downtown Charleston\'s shops, galleries and businesses featuring a variety of art - from paintings and sculptures to  photography and music. ArtWalk is held the third Thursday of each month.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\"><a href=\"http://www.artwalkcwv.com/\" target=\"_blank\">artwalkcwv.com</a></p>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/see-do/city-explorer\" target=\"_blank\"><button style=\"font-family: \'roboto_slabbold\';\">SHARE</button></a>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1242 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/DC_Button_7-G.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />Capitol Market</h3>\r\nBuilt from an 1800s railroad transfer dock, the market serves as an indoor/outdoor farmer\'s market, home of a variety of specialty shops and Sohos restaurant. The Charleston CVB also has a satellite site at the market.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">800 Smith Street\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.capitolmarket.net/\" target=\"_blank\">capitolmarket.net</a></p>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/see-do/city-explorer\" target=\"_blank\"><button style=\"font-family: \'roboto_slabbold\';\">SHARE</button></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1247 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/DC_Button_7-B.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />Live on the Levee</h3>\r\nAn outdoor concert series presented by the City of Charleston, WV. The concerts take place each Friday from Memorial Day Weekend to Labor Day Weekend.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Kanawha Blvd.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://liveontheleveecharleston.com\" target=\"_blank\">liveontheleveecharleston.com</a></p>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/see-do/city-explorer\" target=\"_blank\"><button style=\"font-family: \'roboto_slabbold\';\">SHARE</button></a>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1245 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/DC_Button_7-D.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />Bridge Road Shops</h3>\r\nUnique shops located in a charming neighborhood commercial district. Experience world class dining, shop for your favorite designer clothes, decorate your home with the warmth of one-of-a kind accessories, and experience local and regional art.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\"><a href=\"http://www.bridgeroad.org\" target=\"_blank\">bridgeroad.org</a></p>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/see-do/city-explorer\" target=\"_blank\"><button style=\"font-family: \'roboto_slabbold\';\">SHARE</button></a>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1243 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/DC_Button_7-F.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />Hale Street</h3>\r\nThis hidden street gem offers a unique group of stores and restaurants. Shop at Stray Dog Antiques, get pampered at Tops Off Barber Shop, Salon and Spa, get a smoothie at Mission Savvy Vegan Cafe and dinner at Celsius.<br /><br />\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/see-do/city-explorer\" target=\"_blank\"><button style=\"font-family: \'roboto_slabbold\';\">SHARE</button></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n<div><iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/embed?mid=zF2Ov4mSNUbs.kSaj6sWsDuA4\" width=\"460\" height=\"325\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>',	'City Explorer',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'187-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-08-17 15:06:20',	'2015-08-17 19:06:20',	'',	187,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/187-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(1417,	3,	'2015-08-17 15:08:47',	'2015-08-17 19:08:47',	'<div class=\"content-block col-3-cb\">\r\n<h4>Best Events for Families</h4>\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_253\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"210\"]<a href=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/FestivALL_2014_Childrens_Art_Fair_11_SMALLER_Sava_-__Javins_authorized.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-253\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/FestivALL_2014_Childrens_Art_Fair_11_SMALLER_Sava_-__Javins_authorized-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"FestivALL_2014_Childrens_Art_Fair_11_SMALLER_Sava_-__Javins_authorized\" width=\"210\" height=\"140\" /></a> Children\'s Art Fair. Photo Credit: FestivAll[/caption]\r\n<h3>Clay Center Family Fun Days</h3>\r\nEach day is full of family entertainment with themed science and art activities taking place throughout the day in addition to our three floors of art and science exhibits.\r\n<h3>Children\'s Art Fair and Kanawha County Public Library Street Fair</h3>\r\nA perfect combination for two days of family fun: Make &amp; take craft opportunities from invited artisans and groups, a sale of work by children and youth in Kanawha County neighborhood programs; a stage with child-friendly performances\r\n<h3>Movie Nights at Magic Island</h3>\r\nSponsored by local radio station, WQBE, Magic Island becomes a free, family friendly movie theater under the stars. The Island opens up at 6 with a Kids Zone &amp; the movie will start around dusk! Movie Nights take place Wednesday nights in June.\r\n<h4>Best Time of the Year</h4>\r\nAll year long there\'s plenty of Family Fun in Charleston, WV!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-container-cb\">\r\n<h2>Charleston is a great place for families!  With so many exciting kid-friendly activities including sports, arts and food, theres never a dull moment. For more ideas for family fun, check out our event calendar.</h2>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-1-cb\">\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1212 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/DC_Button_A.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />WV Power</h3>\r\nMinor League baseball team in the South Atlantic League. The Class A Pittsburgh Pirates affiliate plays home games at Appalachian Power Park, also home to the WVSSAC baseball tournament.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Appalachian Power Park\r\n601 Morris St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://wvpower.com\" target=\"_blank\">wvpower.com</a></p>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/see-do/city-explorer\" target=\"_blank\"><button style=\"font-family: \'roboto_slabbold\';\">SHARE</button></a>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1238 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/DC_Button_8-C.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />Public Libraries</h3>\r\nOur local libraries are great places for fun and learning! Many events, programs &amp; services are free to the public. Kanawha County public library also provides geocaching equipment for rent.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">Kanawha County Public Library\r\n123 Capitol St\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://kanawhalibrary.org/\" target=\"_blank\">kanawhalibrary.org</a></p>\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">South Charleston Public Library\r\n312 4th Avenue\r\nSouth Charleston WV 25303\r\n<a href=\"http://www.southcharlestonlibrary.org/\" target=\"_blank\">southcharlestonlibrary.org</a></p>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/see-do/city-explorer\" target=\"_blank\"><button style=\"font-family: \'roboto_slabbold\';\">SHARE</button></a>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1240 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/DC_Button_8-E.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />Chuck E Cheese</h3>\r\nLocated at Southridge Centre, Chuck E. Cheeses is a kid-centric experience. Admission is free and games require tokens that can be purchased. There\'s also a show consisting of characters &amp; music.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">2846 Mountaineer Blvd.\r\nCharleston, WV, 25309\r\n<a href=\"http://www.chuckecheese.com/\" target=\"_blank\">chuckecheese.com</a></p>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/see-do/city-explorer\" target=\"_blank\"><button style=\"font-family: \'roboto_slabbold\';\">SHARE</button></a>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1206 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/DC_Button_8_g.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />Waterways</h3>\r\nWaterways offers pool, tube &amp; body slides, lazy river, walking trail, unlimited putt-putt golf and kiddie island. Shelters available for family outings. Concession food is available for meals and snacks.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">109 Water Way\r\nAlkol, WV 25501\r\n<a href=\"http://waterwayspark.net/\" target=\"_blank\">waterwayspark.net</a></p>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/see-do/city-explorer\" target=\"_blank\"><button style=\"font-family: \'roboto_slabbold\';\">SHARE</button></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"content-block col-2-cb\">\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1237 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/DC_Button_8-B.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />Clay Center for the Arts and      Sciences</h3>\r\nA 240,000 sq ft structure housing performing &amp; visual arts and sciences under one roof. Home to the Avampato Discovery Museum, Juliet Museum of Art and Maier Foundation Performance\r\nHall.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">One Clay Square\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"http://www.theclaycenter.org/\" target=\"_blank\">theclaycenter.org</a></p>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/see-do/city-explorer\" target=\"_blank\"><button style=\"font-family: \'roboto_slabbold\';\">SHARE</button></a>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1239 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/DC_Button_8-D.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />The Peanut Shoppe</h3>\r\nThe Peanut Shoppe has been a Charleston tradition for over 60 years. Established in 1950 by Delbert Moore, it is still in its original location. We recommend the chocolate stars!\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">126 Capitol St.\r\nCharleston, WV 25301\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/thepeanutshoppe\" target=\"_blank\">facebook.com/thepeanutshoppe</a></p>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/see-do/city-explorer\" target=\"_blank\"><button style=\"font-family: \'roboto_slabbold\';\">SHARE</button></a>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1241 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/DC_Button_8-F.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />Camden Park</h3>\r\nLooking for old-fashioned fun? Camden Park, WVs only amusement park, is a 26 acre park located near Huntington. Established in 1903, the park is home to more than thirty rides and attractions, including a full-size traditional wooden roller coaster and several other vintage rides.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">5000 Waverly Rd.\r\nHuntington, WV 25704\r\n<a href=\"http://www.camdenpark.com/\" target=\"_blank\">camdenpark.com</a></p>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/see-do/city-explorer\" target=\"_blank\"><button style=\"font-family: \'roboto_slabbold\';\">SHARE</button></a>\r\n\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-1210 size-full\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/DC_Button_8_h.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />Coonskin Park</h3>\r\nThe park includes over 1,000 acres of hiking/biking trails, an accessible 18 hole golf course, Olympic size pool, picnic shelters, tennis courts, horseshoe pits, playground, ampitheater,\r\nsoccer stadium and wedding garden.\r\n<p class=\"content-block cbaddress\">2000 Coonskin Drive\r\nCharleston, WV 25311\r\n<a href=\"http://www.kcprc.com/Parks/Coonskin-Park.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">Coonskin-Park</a></p>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/see-do/city-explorer\" target=\"_blank\"><button style=\"font-family: \'roboto_slabbold\';\">SHARE</button></a>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\r\n<div><iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/d/embed?mid=zF2Ov4mSNUbs.km_PDXqCqQi8\" width=\"460\" height=\"325\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>',	'Family Fun',	'',	'inherit',	'open',	'open',	'',	'202-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2015-08-17 15:08:47',	'2015-08-17 19:08:47',	'',	202,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/uncategorized/202-revision-v1',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
