(1472,	3,	'2015-08-19 16:23:48',	'2015-08-19 20:23:48',	'12th Annual National Alliance for Drug Endangered Children conference will provide training on the latest research and best practice strategies for drug endangered children efforts at the local, state, tribal, and federal levels. This conference will enable participants to enhance collaborate efforts to protect children from the harmful effects of their caregivers\' substance abuse.\r\n\r\nWe anticipate a nationwide representation of service providers and professionals, including child welfare providers, substance abuse treatment providers, juvenile and family court judges and attorneys, law enforcement, prosecutors, probation officers, prevention specialists, maternal and child health agencies, physicians, nurses, researchers and evaluators, educators, Tribal communities, community organizations serving youth, and children and adult mental health providers.',	'National Alliance for Drug Endangered Children Conference',	'',	'publish',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'national-alliance-for-drug-endangered-children-conference',	'',	'',	'2015-08-19 16:25:21',	'2015-08-19 20:25:21',	'',	0,	'http://localhost:8888/discovercharleston/?post_type=chronosly&#038;p=1472',	0,	'chronosly',	'',	0),
